{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879777887,"sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaee8d1001Dz1AtVaWXy2Mfu","messageID":"msg_d7aaecbef001HBHPz94gu4dZRe","sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","type":"tool","tool":"glob","callID":"toolu_functions.glob:7","state":{"status":"error","input":{"path":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/agentd","pattern":"**/*.go"},"error":"No such file or directory: '/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/agentd'","time":{"start":1775879777883,"end":1775879777887}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879777907,"sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaed82f001ys01ujlEMW4Aok","messageID":"msg_d7aaecbef001HBHPz94gu4dZRe","sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:4","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017 Design: PicoD JWT Middleware\n2: \n3: ## Overview\n4: \n5: **AR ID:** AR-017  \n6: **Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n7: **Language:** Go  \n8: **Size:** S (Small)\n9: \n10: The PicoD JWT Middleware provides authentication for PicoD API endpoints by validating JSON Web Tokens (JWT) on incoming requests. It supports HMAC (HS256) and RSA (RS256) signing algorithms, validates standard claims (expiration, issuer), and integrates with the HTTP middleware chain to protect PicoD command execution endpoints (AR-015).\n11: \n12: This implementation integrates with:\n13: - **PicoD Command Execution (AR-015)**: Provides authentication layer for command execution endpoints\n14: - **Router JWT (existing)**: Uses consistent JWT patterns with the router package\n15: \n16: ---\n17: \n18: ## Architecture\n19: \n20: ### High-Level Design\n21: \n22: ```\n23: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n24: │                         Client Application                                   │\n25: │                    (with JWT from Identity Provider)                         │\n26: └─────────────────────────────────┬───────────────────────────────────────────┘\n27:                                   │\n28:                                   ▼\n29: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n30: │                         HTTP Server Layer                                    │\n31: │  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n32: │  │                     JWTMiddleware                                       │  │\n33: │  │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌───────────┐  │  │\n34: │  │  │   Extract   │──►│   Parse     │──►│   Verify    │──►│ Validate  │  │  │\n35: │  │  │    Token    │   │   Header    │   │  Signature  │   │  Claims   │  │  │\n36: │  │  └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────┬─────┘  │  │\n37: │  │                                                              │        │  │\n38: │  │  ┌───────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘        │  │\n39: │  │  │                                                                   │  │\n40: │  │  ▼                                                                   │  │\n41: │  │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐                │  │\n42: │  │  │    Inject   │──►│    Call     │──►│   Handler   │                │  │\n43: │  │  │   Claims    │   │   Handler   │   │  Response   │                │  │\n44: │  │  │  to Context │   │             │   │             │                │  │\n45: │  │  └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘                │  │\n46: │  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n47: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n48: │                      JWT Validation Layer                                    │\n49: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │\n50: │  │  Token Parser    │  │  Signature Verif │  │  Claims Validator        │   │\n51: │  │  · Header parse  │  │  · HS256 (HMAC)  │  │  · Expiration (exp)      │   │\n52: │  │  · Claims decode │  │  · RS256 (RSA)   │  │  · Issuer (iss)          │   │\n53: │  │  · Algorithm id  │  │  · Key loading   │  │  · Clock skew tolerance  │   │\n54: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │\n55: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n56: │                      Configuration Layer                                     │\n57: │  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │\n58: │  │  Environment     │  │  Secret Loader   │  │  Key Parser              │   │\n59: │  │  · PICOD_JWT_*   │  │  · HMAC secret   │  │  · PEM decoding          │   │\n60: │  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │\n61: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n62: ```\n63: \n64: ### Component Architecture\n65: \n66: ```\n67: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n68: │                       Token Validation Flow                                  │\n69: │                                                                              │\n70: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n71: │  │  Token   │──►│  Parse   │──►│ Validate │──►│  Verify  │──►│ Validate │  │\n72: │  │  Input   │   │  Header  │   │ Algorithm│   │ Signature│   │  Claims  │  │\n73: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘   └────┬─────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n74: │                                     │              │              │        │\n75: │                         ┌───────────┘              │              │        │\n76: │                         │     ┌────────────────────┘              │        │\n77: │                         ▼     ▼                                   ▼        │\n78: │  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n79: │  │  Return  │◀──│  Return  │◀──│  Return  │◀──│  Return  │◀──│  Return  │  │\n80: │  │  Claims  │   │   Err    │   │   Err    │   │   Err    │   │  Claims  │  │\n81: │  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n82: │                                                                              │\n83: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n84: ```\n85: \n86: ### Component Interactions\n87: \n88: | Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n89: |-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n90: | **JWTValidator** | Core interface for token validation | JWT string, ValidationOptions | Parsed Claims or validation error |\n91: | **TokenParser** | Parses JWT header and claims | Raw JWT string | Parsed header and claims |\n92: | **SignatureVerifier** | Verifies token signatures | Token, key material | Verification status |\n93: | **ClaimsValidator** | Validates standard claims | Parsed claims | Validated claims or error |\n94: | **JWTMiddleware** | HTTP middleware wrapper | HTTP request, handler | Authenticated request or HTTP error |\n95: | **ConfigLoader** | Loads environment configuration | Environment variables | ValidationOptions |\n96: \n97: ---\n98: \n99: ## Directory Structure\n100: \n101: ```\n102: pkg/picod/jwt/\n103: ├── types.go              # Claims and options type definitions (~80 lines)\n104: ├── validator.go          # JWTValidator implementation (~150 lines)\n105: ├── middleware.go         # HTTP middleware implementation (~120 lines)\n106: ├── config.go             # Environment-based configuration (~80 lines)\n107: ├── errors.go             # Error type definitions (~60 lines)\n108: ├── validator_test.go     # Unit tests for validator (~200 lines)\n109: └── middleware_test.go    # Unit tests for middleware (~150 lines)\n110: ```\n111: \n112: ---\n113: \n114: ## Data Structures\n115: \n116: ### Request/Response Types\n117: \n118: #### Claims\n119: \n120: ```go\n121: // Claims represents validated JWT claims extracted from a token.\n122: // These claims are propagated to downstream handlers via context.\n123: type Claims struct {\n124:     // Subject is the user/subject identifier\n125:     Subject string `json:\"sub\"`\n126: \n127:     // Issuer identifies the principal that issued the JWT\n128:     Issuer string `json:\"iss\"`\n129: \n130:     // ExpiresAt is the expiration time on or after which the token MUST NOT be accepted\n131:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`\n132: \n133:     // IssuedAt is the time at which the JWT was issued\n134:     IssuedAt time.Time `json:\"iat\"`\n135: }\n136: \n137: // IsExpired checks if the token is expired considering clock skew.\n138: func (c *Claims) IsExpired(clockSkew time.Duration) bool {\n139:     return time.Now().After(c.ExpiresAt.Add(clockSkew))\n140: }\n141: \n142: // IsValidIssuer checks if the issuer matches the expected value.\n143: func (c *Claims) IsValidIssuer(expected string) bool {\n144:     return c.Issuer == expected\n145: }\n146: ```\n147: \n148: #### ValidationOptions\n149: \n150: ```go\n151: // ValidationOptions configures the JWT validator behavior.\n152: type ValidationOptions struct {\n153:     // Algorithm is the expected signing algorithm (\"HS256\" or \"RS256\")\n154:     Algorithm string\n155: \n156:     // Secret is the HMAC secret for HS256 validation\n157:     Secret []byte\n158: \n159:     // PublicKey is the RSA public key for RS256 validation\n160:     PublicKey *rsa.PublicKey\n161: \n162:     // ExpectedIssuer is the required issuer claim value\n163:     ExpectedIssuer string\n164: \n165:     // ClockSkew is the allowed time difference for exp validation\n166:     ClockSkew time.Duration\n167: \n168:     // AllowedAlgs is the whitelist of allowed signing algorithms\n169:     AllowedAlgs []string\n170: }\n171: \n172: // DefaultValidationOptions returns default options with safe defaults.\n173: func DefaultValidationOptions() ValidationOptions {\n174:     return ValidationOptions{\n175:         Algorithm:   \"RS256\",\n176:         ClockSkew:   time.Minute,\n177:         AllowedAlgs: []string{\"HS256\", \"RS256\"},\n178:     }\n179: }\n180: \n181: // Validate checks if the options are valid for use.\n182: func (o *ValidationOptions) Validate() error {\n183:     if o.ExpectedIssuer == \"\" {\n184:         return ErrInvalidConfig\n185:     }\n186:     if o.Algorithm == \"\" {\n187:         return ErrInvalidConfig\n188:     }\n189:     if o.Algorithm == \"HS256\" && len(o.Secret) == 0 {\n190:         return ErrInvalidConfig\n191:     }\n192:     if o.Algorithm == \"RS256\" && o.PublicKey == nil {\n193:         return ErrInvalidConfig\n194:     }\n195:     return nil\n196: }\n197: ```\n198: \n199: #### MiddlewareOptions\n200: \n201: ```go\n202: // MiddlewareOptions configures the JWT middleware behavior.\n203: type MiddlewareOptions struct {\n204:     // Validator is the JWT validator instance\n205:     Validator JWTValidator\n206: \n207:     // ErrorHandler is called for validation errors (optional)\n208:     // If nil, default error responses are used\n209:     ErrorHandler func(http.ResponseWriter, error)\n210: \n211:     // ExcludePaths is a list of paths to exclude from authentication\n212:     ExcludePaths []string\n213: }\n214: \n215: // Validate checks if the middleware options are valid.\n216: func (o *MiddlewareOptions) Validate() error {\n217:     if o.Validator == nil {\n218:         return ErrInvalidConfig\n219:     }\n220:     return nil\n221: }\n222: ```\n223: \n224: ### Domain Types\n225: \n226: #### JWTValidator Interface\n227: \n228: ```go\n229: // JWTValidator validates JWT tokens and returns parsed claims.\n230: type JWTValidator interface {\n231:     // ValidateToken validates a JWT string and returns the parsed claims.\n232:     //\n233:     // Returns:\n234:     //   - *Claims: Parsed claims on successful validation\n235:     //   - error: ErrInvalidTokenFormat, ErrInvalidSignature, ErrTokenExpired,\n236:     //            ErrInvalidIssuer, or ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm\n237:     ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n238: }\n239: \n240: // validator implements JWTValidator.\n241: type validator struct {\n242:     opts ValidationOptions\n243: }\n244: \n245: // NewValidator creates a new JWTValidator with the specified options.\n246: func NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error) {\n247:     if err := opts.Validate(); err != nil {\n248:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: %v\", ErrInvalidConfig, err)\n249:     }\n250:     return &validator{opts: opts}, nil\n251: }\n252: ```\n253: \n254: #### parsedToken (Internal)\n255: \n256: ```go\n257: // parsedToken represents a JWT token after initial parsing.\n258: type parsedToken struct {\n259:     // Header contains the JWT header claims\n260:     Header map[string]interface{}\n261: \n262:     // Claims contains the JWT payload claims\n263:     Claims map[string]interface{}\n264: \n265:     // Signature is the raw signature bytes\n266:     Signature []byte\n267: \n268:     // raw is the original token string\n269:     raw string\n270: }\n271: \n272: // Algorithm extracts the algorithm from the header.\n273: func (t *parsedToken) Algorithm() string {\n274:     if alg, ok := t.Header[\"alg\"].(string); ok {\n275:         return alg\n276:     }\n277:     return \"\"\n278: }\n279: \n280: // extractClaims converts map claims to Claims struct.\n281: func (t *parsedToken) extractClaims() (*Claims, error) {\n282:     claims := &Claims{}\n283: \n284:     // Extract subject\n285:     if sub, ok := t.Claims[\"sub\"].(string); ok {\n286:         claims.Subject = sub\n287:     }\n288: \n289:     // Extract issuer\n290:     if iss, ok := t.Claims[\"iss\"].(string); ok {\n291:         claims.Issuer = iss\n292:     }\n293: \n294:     // Extract expiration\n295:     if exp, ok := t.Claims[\"exp\"].(float64); ok {\n296:         claims.ExpiresAt = time.Unix(int64(exp), 0)\n297:     } else if expStr, ok := t.Claims[\"exp\"].(string); ok {\n298:         if expTime, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, expStr); err == nil {\n299:             claims.ExpiresAt = expTime\n300:         }\n301:     }\n302: \n303:     // Extract issued-at\n304:     if iat, ok := t.Claims[\"iat\"].(float64); ok {\n305:         claims.IssuedAt = time.Unix(int64(iat), 0)\n306:     } else if iatStr, ok := t.Claims[\"iat\"].(string); ok {\n307:         if iatTime, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, iatStr); err == nil {\n308:             claims.IssuedAt = iatTime\n309:         }\n310:     }\n311: \n312:     return claims, nil\n313: }\n314: ```\n315: \n316: ### Internal Types\n317: \n318: #### Config\n319: \n320: ```go\n321: // Config contains environment-based configuration for JWT validation.\n322: type Config struct {\n323:     // Algorithm is the signing algorithm (HS256 or RS256)\n324:     Algorithm string\n325: \n326:     // Secret is the HMAC secret for HS256\n327:     Secret string\n328: \n329:     // PublicKeyPath is the path to the RSA public key file for RS256\n330:     PublicKeyPath string\n331: \n332:     // Issuer is the expected issuer claim\n333:     Issuer string\n334: \n335:     // ClockSkew is the clock skew tolerance duration\n336:     ClockSkew time.Duration\n337: }\n338: \n339: // LoadConfig loads configuration from environment variables.\n340: func LoadConfig() (*Config, error) {\n341:     cfg := &Config{\n342:         Algorithm: getEnvOrDefault(\"PICOD_JWT_ALG\", \"RS256\"),\n343:         Issuer:    os.Getenv(\"PICOD_JWT_ISSUER\"),\n344:         ClockSkew: defaultClockSkew,\n345:     }\n346: \n347:     // Issuer is required\n348:     if cfg.Issuer == \"\" {\n349:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: PICOD_JWT_ISSUER is required\", ErrInvalidConfig)\n350:     }\n351: \n352:     // Parse clock skew\n353:     if skew := os.Getenv(\"PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW\"); skew != \"\" {\n354:         if d, err := time.ParseDuration(skew); err == nil {\n355:             cfg.ClockSkew = d\n356:         } else {\n357:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: invalid PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW: %v\", ErrInvalidConfig, err)\n358:         }\n359:     }\n360: \n361:     // Load algorithm-specific config\n362:     switch cfg.Algorithm {\n363:     case \"HS256\":\n364:         cfg.Secret = os.Getenv(\"PICOD_JWT_SECRET\")\n365:         if cfg.Secret == \"\" {\n366:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: PICOD_JWT_SECRET is required for HS256\", ErrInvalidConfig)\n367:         }\n368:     case \"RS256\":\n369:         cfg.PublicKeyPath = os.Getenv(\"PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY\")\n370:         if cfg.PublicKeyPath == \"\" {\n371:             return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY is required for RS256\", ErrInvalidConfig)\n372:         }\n373:     default:\n374:         return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"%w: unsupported algorithm: %s\", ErrInvalidConfig, cfg.Algorithm)\n375:     }\n376: \n377:     return cfg, nil\n378: }\n379: \n380: // ToValidationOptions converts Config to ValidationOptions.\n381: func (c *Config) ToValidationOptions() (ValidationOptions, error) {\n382:     opts := ValidationOptions{\n383:         Algorithm:      c.Algorithm,\n384:         ExpectedIssuer: c.Issuer,\n385:         ClockSkew:      c.ClockSkew,\n386:         AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\", \"RS256\"},\n387:     }\n388: \n389:     switch c.Algorithm {\n390:     case \"HS256\":\n391:         opts.Secret = []byte(c.Secret)\n392:     case \"RS256\":\n393:         key, err := loadRSAPublicKey(c.PublicKeyPath)\n394:         if err != nil {\n395:             return ValidationOptions{}, fmt.Errorf(\"failed to load RSA public key: %w\", err)\n396:         }\n397:         opts.PublicKey = key\n398:     }\n399: \n400:     return opts, nil\n401: }\n402: ```\n403: \n404: ### Constants\n405: \n406: ```go\n407: // Default configuration values\n408: const (\n409:     // defaultClockSkew is the default clock skew tolerance\n410:     defaultClockSkew = time.Minute\n411: \n412:     // authorizationHeader is the HTTP header name for authorization\n413:     authorizationHeader = \"Authorization\"\n414: \n415:     // bearerPrefix is the expected prefix for bearer tokens\n416:     bearerPrefix = \"Bearer \"\n417: \n418:     // tokenParts is the expected number of JWT parts (header.payload.signature)\n419:     tokenParts = 3\n420: )\n421: \n422: // Error codes for HTTP responses\n423: const (\n424:     // ErrorCodeMissingToken indicates no authorization header\n425:     ErrorCodeMissingToken = \"MISSING_TOKEN\"\n426: \n427:     // ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat indicates malformed JWT\n428:     ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat = \"INVALID_TOKEN_FORMAT\"\n429: \n430:     // ErrorCodeInvalidSignature indicates signature verification failure\n431:     ErrorCodeInvalidSignature = \"INVALID_SIGNATURE\"\n432: \n433:     // ErrorCodeTokenExpired indicates expired token\n434:     ErrorCodeTokenExpired = \"TOKEN_EXPIRED\"\n435: \n436:     // ErrorCodeInvalidIssuer indicates issuer mismatch\n437:     ErrorCodeInvalidIssuer = \"INVALID_ISSUER\"\n438: \n439:     // ErrorCodeUnsupportedAlgorithm indicates unsupported signing algorithm\n440:     ErrorCodeUnsupportedAlgorithm = \"UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM\"\n441: \n442:     // ErrorCodeInvalidConfig indicates configuration error\n443:     ErrorCodeInvalidConfig = \"INVALID_CONFIG\"\n444: )\n445: ```\n446: \n447: ---\n448: \n449: ## API Contracts\n450: \n451: ### JWTValidator Interface\n452: \n453: ```go\n454: // JWTValidator is the primary interface for token validation.\n455: type JWTValidator interface {\n456:     // ValidateToken validates a JWT string and returns parsed claims.\n457:     //\n458:     // Parameters:\n459:     //   - token: The JWT string to validate (must be in header.payload.signature format)\n460:     //\n461:     // Returns:\n462:     //   - *Claims: Parsed claims on successful validation\n463:     //   - error: Validation error with specific error type\n464:     //\n465:     // Errors:\n466:     //   - ErrInvalidTokenFormat: Token is malformed or missing required parts\n467:     //   - ErrInvalidSignature: Signature verification failed\n468:     //   - ErrTokenExpired: Token has expired (considering clock skew)\n469:     //   - ErrInvalidIssuer: Issuer claim doesn't match expected value\n470:     //   - ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm: Token uses an algorithm not in AllowedAlgs\n471:     ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n472: }\n473: \n474: // NewValidator creates a JWTValidator with the specified options.\n475: //\n476: // Parameters:\n477: //   - opts: Validation options including algorithm, keys, and validation rules\n478: //\n479: // Returns:\n480: //   - JWTValidator: Configured validator instance\n481: //   - error: Configuration validation error\n482: func NewValidator(opts ValidationOptions) (JWTValidator, error)\n483: ```\n484: \n485: ### Middleware Functions\n486: \n487: ```go\n488: // JWTMiddleware creates an HTTP middleware for JWT validation.\n489: //\n490: // Parameters:\n491: //   - opts: Middleware configuration including validator and error handler\n492: //\n493: // Returns:\n494: //   - func(http.Handler) http.Handler: Middleware function that wraps handlers\n495: //\n496: // Usage:\n497: //   handler := JWTMiddleware(opts)(myHandler)\n498: func JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n499: \n500: // GetClaims retrieves validated claims from request context.\n501: //\n502: // Parameters:\n503: //   - ctx: Context from an HTTP request that passed through JWTMiddleware\n504: //\n505: // Returns:\n506: //   - *Claims: Parsed JWT claims (nil if not found)\n507: //   - bool: true if claims were found in context\n508: func GetClaims(ctx context.Context) (*Claims, bool)\n509: \n510: // ContextWithClaims adds claims to a context.\n511: //\n512: // Parameters:\n513: //   - ctx: Base context\n514: //   - claims: JWT claims to add\n515: //\n516: // Returns:\n517: //   - context.Context: Context with claims attached\n518: func ContextWithClaims(ctx context.Context, claims *Claims) context.Context\n519: ```\n520: \n521: ### Configuration Functions\n522: \n523: ```go\n524: // LoadConfig loads JWT configuration from environment variables.\n525: //\n526: // Required environment variables:\n527: //   - PICOD_JWT_ISSUER: Expected issuer claim\n528: //\n529: // Required for HS256:\n530: //   - PICOD_JWT_SECRET: HMAC secret\n531: //\n532: // Required for RS256:\n533: //   - PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY: Path to RSA public key PEM file\n534: //\n535: // Optional:\n536: //   - PICOD_JWT_ALG: Algorithm (default: \"RS256\")\n537: //   - PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW: Clock skew tolerance (default: \"1m\")\n538: //\n539: // Returns:\n540: //   - *Config: Loaded configuration\n541: //   - error: Configuration loading error\n542: func LoadConfig() (*Config, error)\n543: \n544: // LoadValidatorFromEnv creates a JWTValidator from environment configuration.\n545: //\n546: // This is a convenience function that loads config and creates a validator.\n547: //\n548: // Returns:\n549: //   - JWTValidator: Configured validator\n550: //   - error: Configuration or initialization error\n551: func LoadValidatorFromEnv() (JWTValidator, error)\n552: ```\n553: \n554: ### Helper Functions\n555: \n556: ```go\n557: // ExtractBearerToken extracts the bearer token from an Authorization header.\n558: //\n559: // Parameters:\n560: //   - header: The Authorization header value\n561: //\n562: // Returns:\n563: //   - string: Extracted token\n564: //   - error: ErrMissingToken or ErrInvalidTokenFormat\n565: func ExtractBearerToken(header string) (string, error)\n566: \n567: // IsExcludedPath checks if a request path should be excluded from auth.\n568: //\n569: // Parameters:\n570: //   - path: Request path\n571: //   - exclusions: List of excluded path patterns\n572: //\n573: // Returns:\n574: //   - bool: true if path should be excluded\n575: func IsExcludedPath(path string, exclusions []string) bool\n576: \n577: // WriteErrorResponse writes a standardized JSON error response.\n578: //\n579: // Parameters:\n580: //   - w: Response writer\n581: //   - status: HTTP status code\n582: //   - code: Error code\n583: //   - message: Human-readable error message\n584: func WriteErrorResponse(w http.ResponseWriter, status int, code, message string)\n585: ```\n586: \n587: ---\n588: \n589: ## Error Handling\n590: \n591: ### Error Categories and Codes\n592: \n593: | Error | Code | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n594: |-------|------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n595: | `ErrMissingToken` | `MISSING_TOKEN` | No Authorization header present | No | Return HTTP 401 |\n596: | `ErrInvalidTokenFormat` | `INVALID_TOKEN_FORMAT` | Malformed JWT structure | No | Return HTTP 401 |\n597: | `ErrInvalidSignature` | `INVALID_SIGNATURE` | Signature verification failed | No | Return HTTP 401 |\n598: | `ErrTokenExpired` | `TOKEN_EXPIRED` | Token has expired | No | Return HTTP 401 |\n599: | `ErrInvalidIssuer` | `INVALID_ISSUER` | Issuer claim mismatch | No | Return HTTP 403 |\n600: | `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm` | `UNSUPPORTED_ALGORITHM` | Algorithm not in allowed list | No | Return HTTP 401 |\n601: | `ErrInvalidConfig` | `INVALID_CONFIG` | Configuration error | No | Fail on startup |\n602: \n603: ### Sentinel Errors\n604: \n605: ```go\n606: // JWT validation errors\n607: var (\n608:     ErrMissingToken         = errors.New(\"jwt: missing bearer token\")\n609:     ErrInvalidTokenFormat   = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid token format\")\n610:     ErrInvalidSignature     = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid signature\")\n611:     ErrTokenExpired         = errors.New(\"jwt: token expired\")\n612:     ErrInvalidIssuer        = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid issuer\")\n613:     ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm = errors.New(\"jwt: unsupported algorithm\")\n614:     ErrInvalidConfig        = errors.New(\"jwt: invalid configuration\")\n615: )\n616: ```\n617: \n618: ### ValidationError Structure\n619: \n620: ```go\n621: // ValidationError represents a JWT validation error with context.\n622: type ValidationError struct {\n623:     // Code is the machine-readable error code\n624:     Code string `json:\"code\"`\n625: \n626:     // Message is the human-readable error message\n627:     Message string `json:\"message\"`\n628: \n629:     // Details contains additional error context\n630:     Details map[string]interface{} `json:\"details,omitempty\"`\n631: \n632:     // underlying is the wrapped error\n633:     underlying error\n634: }\n635: \n636: // Error returns the error string.\n637: func (e *ValidationError) Error() string {\n638:     if e.underlying != nil {\n639:         return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (%v)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.underlying)\n640:     }\n641:     return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s\", e.Code, e.Message)\n642: }\n643: \n644: // Unwrap returns the wrapped error.\n645: func (e *ValidationError) Unwrap() error {\n646:     return e.underlying\n647: }\n648: \n649: // NewValidationError creates a new ValidationError.\n650: func NewValidationError(code, message string, underlying error) *ValidationError {\n651:     return &ValidationError{\n652:         Code:       code,\n653:         Message:    message,\n654:         underlying: underlying,\n655:     }\n656: }\n657: \n658: // WithDetails adds details to the error.\n659: func (e *ValidationError) WithDetails(details map[string]interface{}) *ValidationError {\n660:     e.Details = details\n661:     return e\n662: }\n663: ```\n664: \n665: ### Error Handling Patterns\n666: \n667: #### Token Validation Error Handling\n668: \n669: ```go\n670: func (v *validator) ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error) {\n671:     // Parse the token\n672:     parsed, err := parseToken(token)\n673:     if err != nil {\n674:         return nil, NewValidationError(\n675:             ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat,\n676:             \"failed to parse token\",\n677:             ErrInvalidTokenFormat,\n678:         )\n679:     }\n680: \n681:     // Validate algorithm\n682:     alg := parsed.Algorithm()\n683:     if !v.isAllowedAlgorithm(alg) {\n684:         return nil, NewValidationError(\n685:             ErrorCodeUnsupportedAlgorithm,\n686:             fmt.Sprintf(\"algorithm %s is not allowed\", alg),\n687:             ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm,\n688:         ).WithDetails(map[string]interface{}{\"algorithm\": alg})\n689:     }\n690: \n691:     if alg != v.opts.Algorithm {\n692:         return nil, NewValidationError(\n693:             ErrorCodeUnsupportedAlgorithm,\n694:             fmt.Sprintf(\"expected algorithm %s, got %s\", v.opts.Algorithm, alg),\n695:             ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm,\n696:         )\n697:     }\n698: \n699:     // Verify signature\n700:     if err := v.verifySignature(parsed); err != nil {\n701:         return nil, NewValidationError(\n702:             ErrorCodeInvalidSignature,\n703:             \"signature verification failed\",\n704:             ErrInvalidSignature,\n705:         )\n706:     }\n707: \n708:     // Extract and validate claims\n709:     claims, err := parsed.extractClaims()\n710:     if err != nil {\n711:         return nil, NewValidationError(\n712:             ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat,\n713:             \"failed to extract claims\",\n714:             err,\n715:         )\n716:     }\n717: \n718:     // Check expiration\n719:     if claims.IsExpired(v.opts.ClockSkew) {\n720:         return nil, NewValidationError(\n721:             ErrorCodeTokenExpired,\n722:             \"token has expired\",\n723:             ErrTokenExpired,\n724:         ).WithDetails(map[string]interface{}{\n725:             \"expired_at\": claims.ExpiresAt,\n726:             \"now\":        time.Now(),\n727:         })\n728:     }\n729: \n730:     // Validate issuer\n731:     if !claims.IsValidIssuer(v.opts.ExpectedIssuer) {\n732:         return nil, NewValidationError(\n733:             ErrorCodeInvalidIssuer,\n734:             fmt.Sprintf(\"expected issuer %s, got %s\", v.opts.ExpectedIssuer, claims.Issuer),\n735:             ErrInvalidIssuer,\n736:         ).WithDetails(map[string]interface{}{\n737:             \"expected\": v.opts.ExpectedIssuer,\n738:             \"actual\":   claims.Issuer,\n739:         })\n740:     }\n741: \n742:     return claims, nil\n743: }\n744: ```\n745: \n746: #### Middleware Error Handling\n747: \n748: ```go\n749: func JWTMiddleware(opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler {\n750:     return func(next http.Handler) http.Handler {\n751:         return http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n752:             // Check excluded paths\n753:             if IsExcludedPath(r.URL.Path, opts.ExcludePaths) {\n754:                 next.ServeHTTP(w, r)\n755:                 return\n756:             }\n757: \n758:             // Extract token\n759:             authHeader := r.Header.Get(authorizationHeader)\n760:             if authHeader == \"\" {\n761:                 handleAuthError(w, opts.ErrorHandler, ErrMissingToken)\n762:                 return\n763:             }\n764: \n765:             token, err := ExtractBearerToken(authHeader)\n766:             if err != nil {\n767:                 handleAuthError(w, opts.ErrorHandler, err)\n768:                 return\n769:             }\n770: \n771:             // Validate token\n772:             claims, err := opts.Validator.ValidateToken(token)\n773:             if err != nil {\n774:                 handleAuthError(w, opts.ErrorHandler, err)\n775:                 return\n776:             }\n777: \n778:             // Add claims to context and call next handler\n779:             ctx := ContextWithClaims(r.Context(), claims)\n780:             next.ServeHTTP(w, r.WithContext(ctx))\n781:         })\n782:     }\n783: }\n784: \n785: func handleAuthError(w http.ResponseWriter, handler func(http.ResponseWriter, error), err error) {\n786:     if handler != nil {\n787:         handler(w, err)\n788:         return\n789:     }\n790: \n791:     // Default error handling\n792:     var status int\n793:     var code, message string\n794: \n795:     switch {\n796:     case errors.Is(err, ErrMissingToken):\n797:         status = http.StatusUnauthorized\n798:         code = ErrorCodeMissingToken\n799:         message = \"missing bearer token\"\n800:     case errors.Is(err, ErrInvalidTokenFormat):\n801:         status = http.StatusUnauthorized\n802:         code = ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat\n803:         message = \"invalid token format\"\n804:     case errors.Is(err, ErrInvalidSignature):\n805:         status = http.StatusUnauthorized\n806:         code = ErrorCodeInvalidSignature\n807:         message = \"invalid token signature\"\n808:     case errors.Is(err, ErrTokenExpired):\n809:         status = http.StatusUnauthorized\n810:         code = ErrorCodeTokenExpired\n811:         message = \"token expired\"\n812:     case errors.Is(err, ErrInvalidIssuer):\n813:         status = http.StatusForbidden\n814:         code = ErrorCodeInvalidIssuer\n815:         message = \"invalid issuer\"\n816:     default:\n817:         status = http.StatusUnauthorized\n818:         code = ErrorCodeInvalidTokenFormat\n819:         message = \"authentication failed\"\n820:     }\n821: \n822:     WriteErrorResponse(w, status, code, message)\n823: }\n824: ```\n825: \n826: ---\n827: \n828: ## Testing Strategy\n829: \n830: ### Unit Tests\n831: \n832: #### validator_test.go\n833: \n834: ```go\n835: func TestValidator_ValidateToken_HS256_Success(t *testing.T) {\n836:     // Create validator with HMAC secret\n837:     opts := ValidationOptions{\n838:         Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n839:         Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n840:         ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n841:         ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n842:         AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"},\n843:     }\n844: \n845:     validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n846:     require.NoError(t, err)\n847: \n848:     // Generate valid token\n849:     token := generateTestTokenHS256(\"HS256\", \"test-issuer\", time.Hour)\n850: \n851:     // Validate\n852:     claims, err := validator.ValidateToken(token)\n853:     require.NoError(t, err)\n854:     assert.Equal(t, \"test-user\", claims.Subject)\n855:     assert.Equal(t, \"test-issuer\", claims.Issuer)\n856: }\n857: \n858: func TestValidator_ValidateToken_RS256_Success(t *testing.T) {\n859:     // Load test RSA key\n860:     privateKey, publicKey := generateTestRSAKeys()\n861: \n862:     opts := ValidationOptions{\n863:         Algorithm:      \"RS256\",\n864:         PublicKey:      publicKey,\n865:         ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n866:         ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n867:         AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"RS256\"},\n868:     }\n869: \n870:     validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n871:     require.NoError(t, err)\n872: \n873:     // Generate valid token\n874:     token := generateTestTokenRS256(privateKey, \"test-issuer\", time.Hour)\n875: \n876:     // Validate\n877:     claims, err := validator.ValidateToken(token)\n878:     require.NoError(t, err)\n879:     assert.Equal(t, \"test-user\", claims.Subject)\n880: }\n881: \n882: func TestValidator_ValidateToken_InvalidSignature(t *testing.T) {\n883:     opts := ValidationOptions{\n884:         Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n885:         Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n886:         ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n887:         ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n888:         AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"},\n889:     }\n890: \n891:     validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n892:     require.NoError(t, err)\n893: \n894:     // Generate token with wrong secret\n895:     token := generateTestTokenHS256(\"HS256\", \"test-issuer\", time.Hour, \"wrong-secret\")\n896: \n897:     // Validate\n898:     _, err = validator.ValidateToken(token)\n899:     assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrInvalidSignature)\n900: }\n901: \n902: func TestValidator_ValidateToken_Expired(t *testing.T) {\n903:     opts := ValidationOptions{\n904:         Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n905:         Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n906:         ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n907:         ClockSkew:      0, // No skew\n908:         AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"},\n909:     }\n910: \n911:     validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n912:     require.NoError(t, err)\n913: \n914:     // Generate expired token\n915:     token := generateTestTokenHS256(\"HS256\", \"test-issuer\", -time.Hour)\n916: \n917:     // Validate\n918:     _, err = validator.ValidateToken(token)\n919:     assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrTokenExpired)\n920: }\n921: \n922: func TestValidator_ValidateToken_ClockSkew(t *testing.T) {\n923:     opts := ValidationOptions{\n924:         Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n925:         Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n926:         ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n927:         ClockSkew:      time.Minute * 5, // 5 minute skew\n928:         AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"},\n929:     }\n930: \n931:     validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n932:     require.NoError(t, err)\n933: \n934:     // Generate token expired 30 seconds ago\n935:     token := generateTestTokenHS256(\"HS256\", \"test-issuer\", -time.Second*30)\n936: \n937:     // Should pass with clock skew\n938:     claims, err := validator.ValidateToken(token)\n939:     require.NoError(t, err)\n940:     assert.NotNil(t, claims)\n941: }\n942: \n943: func TestValidator_ValidateToken_WrongIssuer(t *testing.T) {\n944:     opts := ValidationOptions{\n945:         Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n946:         Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n947:         ExpectedIssuer: \"expected-issuer\",\n948:         ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n949:         AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"},\n950:     }\n951: \n952:     validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n953:     require.NoError(t, err)\n954: \n955:     // Generate token with wrong issuer\n956:     token := generateTestTokenHS256(\"HS256\", \"wrong-issuer\", time.Hour)\n957: \n958:     // Validate\n959:     _, err = validator.ValidateToken(token)\n960:     assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrInvalidIssuer)\n961: }\n962: \n963: func TestValidator_ValidateToken_UnsupportedAlgorithm(t *testing.T) {\n964:     opts := ValidationOptions{\n965:         Algorithm:      \"HS256\",\n966:         Secret:         []byte(\"test-secret\"),\n967:         ExpectedIssuer: \"test-issuer\",\n968:         ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n969:         AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"HS256\"}, // Only HS256 allowed\n970:     }\n971: \n972:     validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n973:     require.NoError(t, err)\n974: \n975:     // Generate RS256 token\n976:     _, publicKey := generateTestRSAKeys()\n977:     token := generateTestTokenRS256(nil, \"test-issuer\", time.Hour)\n978: \n979:     // Validate - should fail on algorithm mismatch\n980:     _, err = validator.ValidateToken(token)\n981:     assert.ErrorIs(t, err, ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm)\n982: }\n983: ```\n984: \n985: #### middleware_test.go\n986: \n987: ```go\n988: func TestMiddleware_ValidToken(t *testing.T) {\n989:     // Setup\n990:     mockValidator := &mockJWTValidator{\n991:         validateFunc: func(token string) (*Claims, error) {\n992:             return &Claims{\n993:                 Subject:   \"test-user\",\n994:                 Issuer:    \"test-issuer\",\n995:                 ExpiresAt: time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n996:             }, nil\n997:         },\n998:     }\n999: \n1000:     opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n1001:         Validator: mockValidator,\n1002:     }\n1003: \n1004:     // Create test handler that checks for claims\n1005:     var capturedClaims *Claims\n1006:     handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n1007:         claims, ok := GetClaims(r.Context())\n1008:         if ok {\n1009:             capturedClaims = claims\n1010:         }\n1011:         w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n1012:     })\n1013: \n1014:     // Wrap with middleware\n1015:     wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n1016: \n1017:     // Create request with valid token\n1018:     req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n1019:     req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer valid-token\")\n1020: \n1021:     // Execute\n1022:     rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n1023:     wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n1024: \n1025:     // Assert\n1026:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, rr.Code)\n1027:     assert.NotNil(t, capturedClaims)\n1028:     assert.Equal(t, \"test-user\", capturedClaims.Subject)\n1029: }\n1030: \n1031: func TestMiddleware_MissingToken(t *testing.T) {\n1032:     opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n1033:         Validator: &mockJWTValidator{},\n1034:     }\n1035: \n1036:     handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n1037:         w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n1038:     })\n1039: \n1040:     wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n1041: \n1042:     // Request without Authorization header\n1043:     req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n1044:     rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n1045:     wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n1046: \n1047:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusUnauthorized, rr.Code)\n1048:     assert.Contains(t, rr.Body.String(), \"missing bearer token\")\n1049: }\n1050: \n1051: func TestMiddleware_InvalidFormat(t *testing.T) {\n1052:     opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n1053:         Validator: &mockJWTValidator{},\n1054:     }\n1055: \n1056:     handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n1057:         w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n1058:     })\n1059: \n1060:     wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n1061: \n1062:     // Request with malformed header\n1063:     req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n1064:     req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"InvalidFormat\")\n1065:     rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n1066:     wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n1067: \n1068:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusUnauthorized, rr.Code)\n1069:     assert.Contains(t, rr.Body.String(), \"invalid token format\")\n1070: }\n1071: \n1072: func TestMiddleware_ExpiredToken(t *testing.T) {\n1073:     mockValidator := &mockJWTValidator{\n1074:         validateFunc: func(token string) (*Claims, error) {\n1075:             return nil, ErrTokenExpired\n1076:         },\n1077:     }\n1078: \n1079:     opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n1080:         Validator: mockValidator,\n1081:     }\n1082: \n1083:     handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n1084:         w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n1085:     })\n1086: \n1087:     wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n1088: \n1089:     req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n1090:     req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer expired-token\")\n1091:     rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n1092:     wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n1093: \n1094:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusUnauthorized, rr.Code)\n1095:     assert.Contains(t, rr.Body.String(), \"token expired\")\n1096: }\n1097: \n1098: func TestMiddleware_InvalidIssuer(t *testing.T) {\n1099:     mockValidator := &mockJWTValidator{\n1100:         validateFunc: func(token string) (*Claims, error) {\n1101:             return nil, ErrInvalidIssuer\n1102:         },\n1103:     }\n1104: \n1105:     opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n1106:         Validator: mockValidator,\n1107:     }\n1108: \n1109:     handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n1110:         w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n1111:     })\n1112: \n1113:     wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n1114: \n1115:     req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n1116:     req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer wrong-issuer-token\")\n1117:     rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n1118:     wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n1119: \n1120:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusForbidden, rr.Code)\n1121:     assert.Contains(t, rr.Body.String(), \"invalid issuer\")\n1122: }\n1123: \n1124: func TestMiddleware_ExcludedPath(t *testing.T) {\n1125:     opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n1126:         Validator:    &mockJWTValidator{},\n1127:         ExcludePaths: []string{\"/health\", \"/metrics\"},\n1128:     }\n1129: \n1130:     handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n1131:         w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n1132:     })\n1133: \n1134:     wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n1135: \n1136:     // Request to excluded path without token\n1137:     req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/health\", nil)\n1138:     rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n1139:     wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n1140: \n1141:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, rr.Code)\n1142: }\n1143: \n1144: func TestMiddleware_ContextPropagation(t *testing.T) {\n1145:     expectedClaims := &Claims{\n1146:         Subject:   \"test-user\",\n1147:         Issuer:    \"test-issuer\",\n1148:         ExpiresAt: time.Now().Add(time.Hour),\n1149:     }\n1150: \n1151:     mockValidator := &mockJWTValidator{\n1152:         validateFunc: func(token string) (*Claims, error) {\n1153:             return expectedClaims, nil\n1154:         },\n1155:     }\n1156: \n1157:     opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n1158:         Validator: mockValidator,\n1159:     }\n1160: \n1161:     claimsReceived := false\n1162:     handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n1163:         claims, ok := GetClaims(r.Context())\n1164:         if ok && claims.Subject == expectedClaims.Subject {\n1165:             claimsReceived = true\n1166:         }\n1167:         w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n1168:     })\n1169: \n1170:     wrapped := JWTMiddleware(opts)(handler)\n1171: \n1172:     req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/test\", nil)\n1173:     req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer valid-token\")\n1174:     rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n1175:     wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n1176: \n1177:     assert.True(t, claimsReceived)\n1178: }\n1179: ```\n1180: \n1181: ### Integration Tests\n1182: \n1183: ```go\n1184: func TestIntegration_EndToEnd(t *testing.T) {\n1185:     if testing.Short() {\n1186:         t.Skip(\"Skipping integration test\")\n1187:     }\n1188: \n1189:     // Generate real RSA key pair\n1190:     privateKey, publicKey := generateTestRSAKeys()\n1191: \n1192:     // Create validator\n1193:     opts := ValidationOptions{\n1194:         Algorithm:      \"RS256\",\n1195:         PublicKey:      publicKey,\n1196:         ExpectedIssuer: \"integration-test\",\n1197:         ClockSkew:      time.Minute,\n1198:         AllowedAlgs:    []string{\"RS256\"},\n1199:     }\n1200: \n1201:     validator, err := NewValidator(opts)\n1202:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1203: \n1204:     // Create middleware\n1205:     middlewareOpts := MiddlewareOptions{\n1206:         Validator: validator,\n1207:     }\n1208: \n1209:     // Create handler\n1210:     handler := http.HandlerFunc(func(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\n1211:         claims, ok := GetClaims(r.Context())\n1212:         if !ok {\n1213:             w.WriteHeader(http.StatusInternalServerError)\n1214:             return\n1215:         }\n1216:         w.Header().Set(\"X-User\", claims.Subject)\n1217:         w.WriteHeader(http.StatusOK)\n1218:     })\n1219: \n1220:     wrapped := JWTMiddleware(middlewareOpts)(handler)\n1221: \n1222:     // Generate real token\n1223:     token := generateRealJWT(privateKey, \"RS256\", \"integration-test\", \"test-user\", time.Hour)\n1224: \n1225:     // Make request\n1226:     req := httptest.NewRequest(\"GET\", \"/api/resource\", nil)\n1227:     req.Header.Set(\"Authorization\", \"Bearer \"+token)\n1228:     rr := httptest.NewRecorder()\n1229:     wrapped.ServeHTTP(rr, req)\n1230: \n1231:     // Verify\n1232:     assert.Equal(t, http.StatusOK, rr.Code)\n1233:     assert.Equal(t, \"test-user\", rr.Header().Get(\"X-User\"))\n1234: }\n1235: \n1236: func TestIntegration_Configuration(t *testing.T) {\n1237:     // Set environment variables\n1238:     t.Setenv(\"PICOD_JWT_ISSUER\", \"test-issuer\")\n1239:     t.Setenv(\"PICOD_JWT_SECRET\", \"test-secret\")\n1240:     t.Setenv(\"PICOD_JWT_ALG\", \"HS256\")\n1241:     t.Setenv(\"PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW\", \"2m\")\n1242: \n1243:     // Load configuration\n1244:     cfg, err := LoadConfig()\n1245:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1246:     assert.Equal(t, \"HS256\", cfg.Algorithm)\n1247:     assert.Equal(t, \"test-issuer\", cfg.Issuer)\n1248:     assert.Equal(t, \"test-secret\", cfg.Secret)\n1249:     assert.Equal(t, 2*time.Minute, cfg.ClockSkew)\n1250: \n1251:     // Convert to options\n1252:     opts, err := cfg.ToValidationOptions()\n1253:     require.NoError(t, err)\n1254:     assert.Equal(t, \"HS256\", opts.Algorithm)\n1255:     assert.Equal(t, []byte(\"test-secret\"), opts.Secret)\n1256: }\n1257: ```\n1258: \n1259: ### Test Execution\n1260: \n1261: ```bash\n1262: # Run all JWT middleware tests\n1263: make test PKG=./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n1264: \n1265: # Run with race detector\n1266: go test -race ./pkg/picod/jwt/...\n1267: \n1268: # Run specific test categories\n1269: go test -v ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -run \"TestValidateToken\"\n1270: go test -v ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -run \"TestMiddleware\"\n1271: \n1272: # With coverage\n1273: go test ./pkg/picod/jwt/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\n1274: go tool cover -html=coverage.out\n1275: ```\n1276: \n1277: ---\n1278: \n1279: ## Security Considerations\n1280: \n1281: ### Token Transmission\n1282: - Tokens MUST be transmitted via HTTPS in production\n1283: - HTTP is only allowed in development with appropriate warnings\n1284: - Authorization header is the only supported token transport\n1285: \n1286: ### Key Management\n1287: - HMAC secrets MUST be securely stored (e.g., Kubernetes secrets)\n1288: - RSA public keys should be rotated periodically\n1289: - Private keys for token signing are NOT handled by this middleware\n1290: - Keys should have sufficient length (HMAC: 256+ bits, RSA: 2048+ bits)\n1291: \n1292: ### Validation Security\n1293: - Short token expiration recommended (minutes to hours)\n1294: - Clock skew tolerance kept minimal (default 1 minute)\n1295: - Algorithm explicitly specified to prevent \"none\" algorithm attacks\n1296: - Allowed algorithms whitelist prevents unexpected algorithm usage\n1297: - Path traversal in excluded paths must be handled carefully\n1298: \n1299: ### Implementation Security\n1300: - Constant-time comparison for HMAC verification\n1301: - No sensitive data in error messages\n1302: - Context propagation follows request lifecycle\n1303: - No token logging (only metadata)\n1304: \n1305: ---\n1306: \n1307: ## Performance Considerations\n1308: \n1309: ### Algorithm Performance\n1310: | Algorithm | Relative Speed | Use Case |\n1311: |-----------|----------------|----------|\n1312: | HS256 | Fast (1x) | Internal services, symmetric trust |\n1313: | RS256 | Slower (~10x) | External clients, asymmetric trust |\n1314: \n1315: ### Optimization Strategies\n1316: - RSA signature verification is slower than HMAC\n1317: - Consider caching parsed keys (done at initialization)\n1318: - Minimize allocations in hot path (token validation)\n1319: - Early rejection for missing headers (before validation)\n1320: - Excluded paths bypass validation entirely\n1321: \n1322: ### Resource Usage\n1323: - Memory: Minimal (only stores key material and config)\n1324: - CPU: Depends on algorithm (HS256 < RS256)\n1325: - Network: None (validation is local)\n1326: \n1327: ---\n1328: \n1329: ## Integration Points\n1330: \n1331: ### With PicoD Command Execution (AR-015)\n1332: \n1333: ```go\n1334: // Example: Applying JWT middleware to PicoD API routes\n1335: func SetupPicoDRoutes(mux *http.ServeMux, validator JWTValidator) {\n1336:     opts := MiddlewareOptions{\n1337:         Validator:    validator,\n1338:         ExcludePaths: []string{\"/health\", \"/ready\"},\n1339:     }\n1340: \n1341:     // Apply middleware to protected routes\n1342:     mux.Handle(\"/api/v1/exec\", JWTMiddleware(opts)(execHandler))\n1343:     mux.Handle(\"/api/v1/status\", JWTMiddleware(opts)(statusHandler))\n1344:     mux.Handle(\"/api/v1/logs\", JWTMiddleware(opts)(logsHandler))\n1345: \n1346:     // Public routes (no middleware)\n1347:     mux.Handle(\"/health\", healthHandler)\n1348:     mux.Handle(\"/ready\", readyHandler)\n1349: }\n1350: ```\n1351: \n1352: ### With Existing Router JWT\n1353: \n1354: The PicoD JWT middleware uses consistent patterns with `pkg/router/jwt_*.go`:\n1355: - Similar Claims structure\n1356: - Compatible error handling\n1357: - Consistent context key usage\n1358: \n1359: ---\n1360: \n1361: ## Dependencies\n1362: \n1363: ```go\n1364: import (\n1365:     \"context\"\n1366:     \"crypto/rsa\"\n1367:     \"errors\"\n1368:     \"fmt\"\n1369:     \"net/http\"\n1370:     \"os\"\n1371:     \"strings\"\n1372:     \"time\"\n1373: \n1374:     \"github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5\"\n1375: )\n1376: ```\n1377: \n1378: | Package | Purpose | Version |\n1379: |---------|---------|---------|\n1380: | `github.com/golang-jwt/jwt/v5` | JWT parsing and validation | v5.2.1 |\n1381: | Standard library | Crypto, HTTP, context | Go 1.23+ |\n1382: \n1383: ---\n1384: \n1385: ## References\n1386: \n1387: - [PicoD JWT Design](changes/AR-017/design.md) — Short design document\n1388: - [PicoD JWT Delta Spec](changes/AR-017/delta-spec.md) — API specification\n1389: - [PicoD JWT Tests](changes/AR-017/tests.md) — Test specifications\n1390: - [PicoD JWT Plan](changes/AR-017/plan.md) — Implementation plan\n1391: - [AR-015 Command Execution](changes/AR-015/design.md) — Base API protected by this middleware\n1392: - [RFC 7519](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7519) — JSON Web Token (JWT)\n1393: - [RFC 7515](https://tools.ietf.org/html/rfc7515) — JSON Web Signature (JWS)\n1394: \n1395: ---\n1396: \n1397: *AR-017 — Module: pkg/picod/jwt — Language: Go — Size: S*\n\n(End of file - total 1397 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017 Design: PicoD JWT Middleware\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-017  \n**Module:** `pkg/picod/jwt`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S (Small)\n\nThe PicoD JWT Middleware provides authentication for PicoD API endpoints by validating JSON Web Tokens (JWT) on incoming requests. It supports HMAC (HS256) and RSA (RS256) signing algorithms, validates standard claims (expiration, issuer), and integrates with the HTTP middleware chain to protect PicoD command execution endpoints (AR-015).\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **PicoD Command Execution (AR-015)**: Provides authentication layer for command execution endpoints\n- **Router JWT (existing)**: Uses consistent JWT patterns with the router package\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775879777873,"end":1775879777903}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879777910,"sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaedd7d001XB2AIf9H31GBIJ","messageID":"msg_d7aaecbef001HBHPz94gu4dZRe","sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:5","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # Idle Cleanup — Design\n2: \n3: ## Module\n4: \n5: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n6: \n7: ## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n8: \n9: ### Time threshold\n10: \n11: ```go\n12: var SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n13: ```\n14: \n15: Idle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n16: \n17: ### Annotation key\n18: \n19: The reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n20: \n21: - Import: `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager`\n22: - Key: `workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey` = **`\"last-activity-time\"`**\n23: \n24: (Workload manager also sets `runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout` on Sandbox metadata for template-driven idle configuration; **agentd** only reads `last-activity-time`.)\n25: \n26: ### Reconciler\n27: \n28: ```go\n29: package agentd\n30: \n31: type Reconciler struct {\n32:     client.Client\n33:     Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n34: }\n35: \n36: func (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req ctrl.Request) (ctrl.Result, error)\n37: ```\n38: \n39: **Algorithm (exact behavior):**\n40: \n41: 1. `sandbox := &sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}`; `Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, sandbox)`.\n42: 2. If `errors.IsNotFound(err)` → `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`.\n43: 3. If other get error → return `ctrl.Result{}, err`.\n44: 4. `lastActivityStr, exists := sandbox.Annotations[workloadmanager.LastActivityAnnotationKey]`.\n45: 5. If `exists && lastActivityStr != \"\"`:\n46:    - `lastActivity, err := time.Parse(time.RFC3339, lastActivityStr)`\n47:    - If parse err → `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: 30 * time.Second}, err`\n48:    - `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`\n49:    - If `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`:\n50:      - `r.Delete(ctx, sandbox)`; if err and not `IsNotFound` → `return ctrl.Result{}, err`\n51:    - Else:\n52:      - `return ctrl.Result{RequeueAfter: time.Until(expirationTime)}, nil`\n53: 6. `return ctrl.Result{}, nil`\n54: \n55: ### SetupWithManager\n56: \n57: ```go\n58: func (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n59:     return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n60:         For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n61:         Complete(r)\n62: }\n63: ```\n64: \n65: ## Binary `cmd/agentd/main.go`\n66: \n67: ### Scheme registration\n68: \n69: ```go\n70: var schemeBuilder = runtime.NewScheme()\n71: \n72: func init() {\n73:     utilruntime.Must(scheme.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n74:     utilruntime.Must(sandboxv1alpha1.AddToScheme(schemeBuilder))\n75: }\n76: ```\n77: \n78: ### Controller-runtime manager\n79: \n80: ```go\n81: mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(ctrl.GetConfigOrDie(), ctrl.Options{\n82:     Scheme:                 schemeBuilder,\n83:     Metrics:                metricsserver.Options{BindAddress: \"0\"},\n84:     HealthProbeBindAddress:   \"0\",\n85: })\n86: ```\n87: \n88: ### Controller registration (duplicate of SetupWithManager pattern)\n89: \n90: ```go\n91: err = ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n92:     For(&sandboxv1alpha1.Sandbox{}).\n93:     Complete(&agentd.Reconciler{\n94:         Client: mgr.GetClient(),\n95:         Scheme: mgr.GetScheme(),\n96:     })\n97: ```\n98: \n99: ### Run\n100: \n101: ```go\n102: mgr.Start(ctrl.SetupSignalHandler())\n103: ```\n104: \n105: ## Watched resources\n106: \n107: | API group | Version | Kind | Trigger |\n108: |-----------|---------|------|---------|\n109: | `agents.x-k8s.io` | `v1alpha1` | `Sandbox` | Default `For()` watch — creates, updates, deletes (per controller-runtime) |\n110: \n111: No explicit `Owns` or `Watches` — single primary resource `Sandbox`.\n112: \n113: ## Related workload-manager constants (context)\n114: \n115: From `pkg/workloadmanager` (not used by agentd reconcile logic but set when sandboxes are created):\n116: \n117: - `IdleTimeoutAnnotationKey = \"runtime.agentcube.io/idle-timeout\"` — duration string on Sandbox CR.\n118: - `LastActivityAnnotationKey = \"last-activity-time\"` — **read by agentd** for idle cleanup.\n119: \n120: ## Dependencies\n121: \n122: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors`\n123: - `k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime`\n124: - `sigs.k8s.io/agent-sandbox/api/v1alpha1`\n125: - `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime`\n126: - `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/workloadmanager` (annotation key only)\n\n(End of file - total 126 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# Idle Cleanup — Design\n\n## Module\n\n- `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube` (see root `go.mod` in sandbox-orchestration design).\n\n## Package `github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/agentd`\n\n### Time threshold\n\n```go\nvar SessionExpirationTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n```\n\nIdle expiration: `expirationTime := lastActivity.Add(SessionExpirationTimeout)`; delete when `time.Now().After(expirationTime)`.\n\n### Annotation key\n\nThe reconciler uses the same key as workload manager pod annotation for idle timeout tracking on the **Sandbox** object:\n","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md","time":{"start":1775879777878,"end":1775879777908}}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879777922,"sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaee2be001uzqu8TMDCj0xFg","messageID":"msg_d7aaecbef001HBHPz94gu4dZRe","sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:6","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: /*\n2: Copyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n3: \n4: Licensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\n5: you may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\n6: You may obtain a copy of the License at\n7: \n8:     http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n9: \n10: Unless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\n11: distributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\n12: WITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\n13: See the License for the specific language governing permissions and\n14: limitations under the License.\n15: */\n16: \n17: package v1alpha1\n18: \n19: import (\n20: \tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n21: \tmetav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n22: )\n23: \n24: // AgentRuntimePhase represents the current phase of an AgentRuntime.\n25: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Pending;Running;Succeeded;Failed;Unknown\n26: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n27: type AgentRuntimePhase string\n28: \n29: const (\n30: \t// AgentRuntimePhasePending indicates the sandbox is being created.\n31: \tAgentRuntimePhasePending AgentRuntimePhase = \"Pending\"\n32: \n33: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseRunning indicates the sandbox is active and running.\n34: \tAgentRuntimePhaseRunning AgentRuntimePhase = \"Running\"\n35: \n36: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseSucceeded indicates the sandbox completed successfully.\n37: \tAgentRuntimePhaseSucceeded AgentRuntimePhase = \"Succeeded\"\n38: \n39: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseFailed indicates the sandbox failed.\n40: \tAgentRuntimePhaseFailed AgentRuntimePhase = \"Failed\"\n41: \n42: \t// AgentRuntimePhaseUnknown indicates the sandbox state is unknown.\n43: \tAgentRuntimePhaseUnknown AgentRuntimePhase = \"Unknown\"\n44: )\n45: \n46: // AgentRuntimeConditionType represents a condition type for AgentRuntime.\n47: // +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=Ready;SandboxCreated;SandboxReady;Failed\n48: // +kubebuilder:validation:Type=string\n49: type AgentRuntimeConditionType string\n50: \n51: const (\n52: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionReady indicates the AgentRuntime is ready to accept requests.\n53: \tAgentRuntimeConditionReady AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"Ready\"\n54: \n55: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated indicates the sandbox has been created.\n56: \tAgentRuntimeConditionSandboxCreated AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"SandboxCreated\"\n57: \n58: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionSandboxReady indicates the sandbox is ready for use.\n59: \tAgentRuntimeConditionSandboxReady AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"SandboxReady\"\n60: \n61: \t// AgentRuntimeConditionFailed indicates the AgentRuntime has failed.\n62: \tAgentRuntimeConditionFailed AgentRuntimeConditionType = \"Failed\"\n63: )\n64: \n65: // AgentRuntimeSpec defines the desired state of AgentRuntime.\n66: // This specification describes the configuration for a sandbox instance\n67: // that will run an AI agent.\n68: type AgentRuntimeSpec struct {\n69: \t// Image is the container image to use for the sandbox.\n70: \t// This field is required and must be a valid container image reference.\n71: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n72: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:MinLength=1\n73: \tImage string `json:\"image\"`\n74: \n75: \t// Resources defines the compute resources (CPU, memory) for the sandbox.\n76: \t// If not specified, default resource limits will be applied.\n77: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n78: \tResources *corev1.ResourceRequirements `json:\"resources,omitempty\"`\n79: \n80: \t// Env defines environment variables to set in the sandbox container.\n81: \t// These variables will be available to the running agent.\n82: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n83: \t// +listType=map\n84: \t// +listMapKey=name\n85: \tEnv []corev1.EnvVar `json:\"env,omitempty\"`\n86: \n87: \t// Command overrides the default container entrypoint.\n88: \t// If not specified, the image's default entrypoint will be used.\n89: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n90: \tCommand []string `json:\"command,omitempty\"`\n91: \n92: \t// Args provides arguments to the command or the default entrypoint.\n93: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n94: \tArgs []string `json:\"args,omitempty\"`\n95: \n96: \t// WorkingDir specifies the working directory for the container.\n97: \t// If not specified, the container's default working directory will be used.\n98: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n99: \tWorkingDir string `json:\"workingDir,omitempty\"`\n100: \n101: \t// Ports defines the ports to expose from the sandbox container.\n102: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n103: \t// +listType=map\n104: \t// +listMapKey=containerPort\n105: \tPorts []corev1.ContainerPort `json:\"ports,omitempty\"`\n106: \n107: \t// VolumeMounts defines volumes to mount into the sandbox container.\n108: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n109: \t// +listType=map\n110: \t// +listMapKey=name\n111: \tVolumeMounts []corev1.VolumeMount `json:\"volumeMounts,omitempty\"`\n112: \n113: \t// Volumes defines the volumes that can be mounted by the sandbox.\n114: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n115: \t// +listType=map\n116: \t// +listMapKey=name\n117: \tVolumes []corev1.Volume `json:\"volumes,omitempty\"`\n118: \n119: \t// ServiceAccountName specifies the service account to use for the sandbox pod.\n120: \t// If not specified, the default service account will be used.\n121: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n122: \tServiceAccountName string `json:\"serviceAccountName,omitempty\"`\n123: \n124: \t// NodeSelector specifies node labels for pod scheduling.\n125: \t// The pod will only be scheduled on nodes matching these labels.\n126: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n127: \t// +mapType=atomic\n128: \tNodeSelector map[string]string `json:\"nodeSelector,omitempty\"`\n129: \n130: \t// Tolerations allow the pod to be scheduled on nodes with matching taints.\n131: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n132: \t// +listType=atomic\n133: \tTolerations []corev1.Toleration `json:\"tolerations,omitempty\"`\n134: \n135: \t// Affinity defines the scheduling constraints for the pod.\n136: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n137: \tAffinity *corev1.Affinity `json:\"affinity,omitempty\"`\n138: \n139: \t// TTLSecondsAfterFinished specifies the time to live (in seconds) after\n140: \t// the sandbox has finished (succeeded or failed). The sandbox will be\n141: \t// automatically deleted after this time.\n142: \t// If not specified, the sandbox will not be automatically deleted.\n143: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n144: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n145: \tTTLSecondsAfterFinished *int32 `json:\"ttlSecondsAfterFinished,omitempty\"`\n146: \n147: \t// IdleTimeoutSeconds specifies the maximum time (in seconds) the sandbox\n148: \t// can be idle before being terminated. If not specified, no idle timeout\n149: \t// is enforced.\n150: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n151: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n152: \tIdleTimeoutSeconds *int32 `json:\"idleTimeoutSeconds,omitempty\"`\n153: \n154: \t// MaxLifetimeSeconds specifies the maximum lifetime (in seconds) of the sandbox.\n155: \t// The sandbox will be terminated after this duration regardless of activity.\n156: \t// If not specified, no maximum lifetime is enforced.\n157: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n158: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=1\n159: \tMaxLifetimeSeconds *int32 `json:\"maxLifetimeSeconds,omitempty\"`\n160: }\n161: \n162: // AgentRuntimeStatus defines the observed state of AgentRuntime.\n163: // This status is updated by the controller to reflect the current\n164: // state of the sandbox instance.\n165: type AgentRuntimeStatus struct {\n166: \t// Phase represents the current phase of the AgentRuntime.\n167: \t// Possible values: Pending, Running, Succeeded, Failed, Unknown.\n168: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n169: \tPhase AgentRuntimePhase `json:\"phase,omitempty\"`\n170: \n171: \t// Conditions represents the latest available observations of the AgentRuntime's state.\n172: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n173: \t// +listType=map\n174: \t// +listMapKey=type\n175: \t// +patchMergeKey=type\n176: \t// +patchStrategy=merge\n177: \tConditions []AgentRuntimeCondition `json:\"conditions,omitempty\"`\n178: \n179: \t// SandboxID is the unique identifier of the created sandbox pod.\n180: \t// This is set once the sandbox pod has been successfully created.\n181: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n182: \tSandboxID string `json:\"sandboxId,omitempty\"`\n183: \n184: \t// PodName is the name of the pod running the sandbox.\n185: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n186: \tPodName string `json:\"podName,omitempty\"`\n187: \n188: \t// PodIP is the IP address assigned to the sandbox pod.\n189: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n190: \tPodIP string `json:\"podIP,omitempty\"`\n191: \n192: \t// StartTime is the time when the sandbox was started.\n193: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n194: \tStartTime *metav1.Time `json:\"startTime,omitempty\"`\n195: \n196: \t// CompletionTime is the time when the sandbox completed (succeeded or failed).\n197: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n198: \tCompletionTime *metav1.Time `json:\"completionTime,omitempty\"`\n199: \n200: \t// LastActivityTime is the time of the last activity in the sandbox.\n201: \t// Used for idle timeout tracking.\n202: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n203: \tLastActivityTime *metav1.Time `json:\"lastActivityTime,omitempty\"`\n204: \n205: \t// Message provides a human-readable description of the current status.\n206: \t// This may contain error messages or other status information.\n207: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n208: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n209: \n210: \t// Reason provides a brief reason for the current phase.\n211: \t// This is typically a CamelCase string indicating why the phase is set.\n212: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n213: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n214: \n215: \t// ObservedGeneration is the most recent generation observed by the controller.\n216: \t// This is used to determine if the spec has been processed.\n217: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n218: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Minimum=0\n219: \tObservedGeneration int64 `json:\"observedGeneration,omitempty\"`\n220: }\n221: \n222: // AgentRuntimeCondition represents a condition of an AgentRuntime.\n223: type AgentRuntimeCondition struct {\n224: \t// Type is the type of the condition.\n225: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n226: \tType AgentRuntimeConditionType `json:\"type\"`\n227: \n228: \t// Status is the status of the condition (True, False, Unknown).\n229: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n230: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Enum=True;False;Unknown\n231: \tStatus corev1.ConditionStatus `json:\"status\"`\n232: \n233: \t// LastTransitionTime is the last time the condition transitioned.\n234: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n235: \tLastTransitionTime metav1.Time `json:\"lastTransitionTime,omitempty\"`\n236: \n237: \t// Reason is a brief reason for the condition's last transition.\n238: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n239: \tReason string `json:\"reason,omitempty\"`\n240: \n241: \t// Message is a human-readable message indicating details about the transition.\n242: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n243: \tMessage string `json:\"message,omitempty\"`\n244: }\n245: \n246: // +genclient\n247: // +genclient:noStatus\n248: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n249: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n250: // +kubebuilder:resource:path=agentruntimes,shortName=ar;ars,singular=agentruntime,categories={agentcube,all}\n251: // +kubebuilder:subresource:status\n252: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Phase\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.phase`,description=\"Current phase of the agent runtime\"\n253: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Sandbox\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.sandboxId`,description=\"ID of the sandbox pod\"\n254: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Age\",type=date,JSONPath=`.metadata.creationTimestamp`,description=\"Time since creation\"\n255: // +kubebuilder:printcolumn:name=\"Message\",type=string,JSONPath=`.status.message`,priority=1\n256: \n257: // AgentRuntime is the Schema for the agentruntimes API.\n258: // An AgentRuntime represents a sandbox instance for running AI agents.\n259: // The controller creates and manages the lifecycle of the underlying\n260: // sandbox pod based on this resource.\n261: type AgentRuntime struct {\n262: \tmetav1.TypeMeta   `json:\",inline\"`\n263: \tmetav1.ObjectMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n264: \n265: \t// Spec defines the desired state of the AgentRuntime.\n266: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n267: \tSpec AgentRuntimeSpec `json:\"spec,omitempty\"`\n268: \n269: \t// Status defines the observed state of the AgentRuntime.\n270: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Optional\n271: \tStatus AgentRuntimeStatus `json:\"status,omitempty\"`\n272: }\n273: \n274: // +k8s:deepcopy-gen:interfaces=k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime.Object\n275: // +kubebuilder:object:root=true\n276: \n277: // AgentRuntimeList contains a list of AgentRuntime resources.\n278: type AgentRuntimeList struct {\n279: \tmetav1.TypeMeta `json:\",inline\"`\n280: \tmetav1.ListMeta `json:\"metadata,omitempty\"`\n281: \n282: \t// Items is the list of AgentRuntime resources.\n283: \t// +kubebuilder:validation:Required\n284: \tItems []AgentRuntime `json:\"items\"`\n285: }\n\n(End of file - total 285 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"/*\nCopyright 2026 The Volcano Authors.\n\nLicensed under the Apache License, Version 2.0 (the \"License\");\nyou may not use this file except in compliance with the License.\nYou may obtain a copy of the License at\n\n    http://www.apache.org/licenses/LICENSE-2.0\n\nUnless required by applicable law or agreed to in writing, software\ndistributed under the License is distributed on an \"AS IS\" BASIS,\nWITHOUT WARRANTIES OR CONDITIONS OF ANY KIND, either express or implied.\nSee the License for the specific language governing permissions and\nlimitations under the License.\n*/\n\npackage v1alpha1\n\nimport (\n\tcorev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go","time":{"start":1775879777880,"end":1775879777919}}}}
