{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775879791829,"sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaf153b001u6BmnAg9BFZ460","messageID":"msg_d7aaeeec2001r1EyCF6ZgGt02z","sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","type":"tool","tool":"read","callID":"toolu_functions.read:8","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md"},"output":"<path>/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md</path>\n<type>file</type>\n<content>\n1: # AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Design Document\n2: \n3: ## Purpose\n4: \n5: Define the architecture and design of the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer in the agentcube platform.\n6: \n7: ## Architecture\n8: \n9: ### Components\n10: \n11: ```\n12: ┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n13: │                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n14: ├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n15: │  HTTP Handler ──────► JWT Middleware ──────► Handler    │\n16: │                           │                              │\n17: │                           ▼                              │\n18: │                   Token Validation                       │\n19: │                   (Signature + Claims)                   │\n20: └─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n21: ```\n22: \n23: ### Middleware Flow\n24: \n25: ```\n26: Incoming Request\n27:        │\n28:        ▼\n29: ┌──────────────┐\n30: │ Extract      │\n31: │ Bearer Token │\n32: └──────────────┘\n33:        │\n34:        ▼\n35: ┌──────────────┐\n36: │ Validate     │\n37: │ Token Format │\n38: └──────────────┘\n39:        │\n40:        ▼\n41: ┌──────────────┐\n42: │ Verify       │\n43: │ Signature    │\n44: └──────────────┘\n45:        │\n46:        ▼\n47: ┌──────────────┐\n48: │ Validate     │\n49: │ Claims       │\n50: │ (exp, iss)   │\n51: └──────────────┘\n52:        │\n53:        ▼\n54:    [Valid] ────► Call Handler\n55:        │\n56:    [Invalid] ──► Return 401/403\n57: ```\n58: \n59: ## Key Interfaces\n60: \n61: ### JWTValidator\n62: \n63: Core interface for token validation.\n64: \n65: ```go\n66: type JWTValidator interface {\n67:     // ValidateToken validates a JWT string and returns the parsed claims\n68:     ValidateToken(token string) (*Claims, error)\n69: }\n70: ```\n71: \n72: ### Middleware Function\n73: \n74: ```go\n75: // Middleware wraps an HTTP handler with JWT validation\n76: func JWTMiddleware(validator JWTValidator, opts MiddlewareOptions) func(http.Handler) http.Handler\n77: ```\n78: \n79: ### Claims Structure\n80: \n81: ```go\n82: type Claims struct {\n83:     Subject   string    `json:\"sub\"`\n84:     Issuer    string    `json:\"iss\"`\n85:     ExpiresAt time.Time `json:\"exp\"`\n86:     IssuedAt  time.Time `json:\"iat\"`\n87: }\n88: ```\n89: \n90: ### Validation Options\n91: \n92: ```go\n93: type ValidationOptions struct {\n94:     Issuer        string        // Expected issuer claim\n95:     ClockSkew     time.Duration // Allowed clock skew for exp validation\n96:     AllowedAlgs   []string      // Allowed signing algorithms\n97: }\n98: ```\n99: \n100: ## Supported Algorithms\n101: \n102: | Algorithm | Type | Key Format |\n103: |-----------|------|------------|\n104: | HS256 | HMAC-SHA256 | []byte (symmetric) |\n105: | RS256 | RSA-SHA256 | *rsa.PublicKey |\n106: \n107: ## Configuration\n108: \n109: ### Environment Variables\n110: \n111: | Variable | Required | Default | Description |\n112: |----------|----------|---------|-------------|\n113: | `PICOD_JWT_SECRET` | HS256 only | - | HMAC secret for HS256 |\n114: | `PICOD_JWT_PUBLIC_KEY` | RS256 only | - | Path to RSA public key file |\n115: | `PICOD_JWT_ISSUER` | Yes | - | Expected issuer claim |\n116: | `PICOD_JWT_CLOCK_SKEW` | No | 1m | Clock skew tolerance |\n117: | `PICOD_JWT_ALG` | No | RS256 | Signing algorithm |\n118: \n119: ## Error Handling\n120: \n121: ### Error Types\n122: \n123: - `ErrMissingToken`: No Authorization header present\n124: - `ErrInvalidTokenFormat`: Malformed Authorization header\n125: - `ErrInvalidSignature`: Signature verification failed\n126: - `ErrTokenExpired`: Token has expired\n127: - `ErrInvalidIssuer`: Issuer claim mismatch\n128: - `ErrUnsupportedAlgorithm`: Algorithm not in allowed list\n129: \n130: ### HTTP Responses\n131: \n132: | Scenario | Status | Body |\n133: |----------|--------|------|\n134: | Missing token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"missing bearer token\"}` |\n135: | Invalid signature | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"invalid token signature\"}` |\n136: | Expired token | 401 | `{\"error\": \"unauthorized\", \"message\": \"token expired\"}` |\n137: | Invalid issuer | 403 | `{\"error\": \"forbidden\", \"message\": \"invalid issuer\"}` |\n138: \n139: ## Security Considerations\n140: \n141: - Tokens must be transmitted via HTTPS\n142: - HMAC secrets must be securely stored\n143: - RSA public keys should be rotated periodically\n144: - Short token expiration recommended\n145: - Clock skew tolerance kept minimal\n146: \n147: ## Performance Considerations\n148: \n149: - RSA signature verification is slower than HMAC\n150: - Consider caching parsed keys\n151: - Minimize allocations in hot path\n152: - Early rejection for missing headers\n153: \n154: ## Open Questions\n155: \n156: 1. Should we support JWKS (JSON Web Key Set) for key rotation?\n157: 2. Do we need audience claim validation?\n158: 3. Should we support multiple issuers?\n159: 4. Is token binding to specific endpoints required?\n\n(End of file - total 159 lines)\n</content>","metadata":{"preview":"# AR-017: PicoD JWT 中间件 - Design Document\n\n## Purpose\n\nDefine the architecture and design of the JWT authentication middleware for the PicoD API layer in the agentcube platform.\n\n## Architecture\n\n### Components\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                    PicoD API Layer                       │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│  HTTP Handler ──────► JWT Middleware ──────► Handler    │\n│                           │                              │\n│                           ▼                              │\n│                   Token Validation                       │\n│                   (Signature + Claims)                   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘","truncated":false,"loaded":[]},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/changes/AR-017/design.md","time":{"start":1775879791809,"end":1775879791827}}}}
