{"type":"text","timestamp":1775879801086,"sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaf44ca0015hOEW69Byo2q54","messageID":"msg_d7aaf2509001tZ60BWqPaXIOpS","sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","type":"text","text":"Now I have a clear understanding of the project structure. Let me create the design document for AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller. I'll follow the same comprehensive format as the existing design documents.","time":{"start":1775879801084,"end":1775879801084}}}
{"type":"text","timestamp":1775880056186,"sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab00d63001nR0ZHnBI75uX4C","messageID":"msg_d7aaf2509001tZ60BWqPaXIOpS","sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","type":"text","text":" Clock","time":{"start":1775880056183,"end":1775880056183}}}
{"type":"tool_use","timestamp":1775880056717,"sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","part":{"id":"prt_d7aaf48ff001NY03Xmof57U4il","messageID":"msg_d7aaf2509001tZ60BWqPaXIOpS","sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","type":"tool","tool":"write","callID":"toolu_functions.write:11","state":{"status":"completed","input":{"filePath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","content":"# AR-018 Design: Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller\n\n## Overview\n\n**AR ID:** AR-018  \n**Module:** `pkg/agentd`  \n**Language:** Go  \n**Size:** S (Small)\n\nThe Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller is a Kubernetes controller that automatically deletes AgentRuntime resources that have exceeded their configured idle timeout. It monitors the `LastActivityTime` field in AgentRuntime status and compares it against the `IdleTimeoutSeconds` specified in the spec to determine when a resource should be cleaned up.\n\nThis implementation integrates with:\n- **AgentRuntime API (pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1)**: Watches AgentRuntime resources\n- **client-go library**: Uses generated Kubernetes clientset for API interactions\n- **controller-runtime**: Manages the controller lifecycle and reconciliation loop\n\n---\n\n## Architecture\n\n### High-Level Design\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                         Kubernetes Cluster                                   │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                         AgentRuntime Resources                          │  │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐                    │  │\n│  │  │  Runtime 1  │  │  Runtime 2  │  │  Runtime N  │                    │  │\n│  │  │ (active)    │  │ (idle 20m)  │  │ (idle 45m)  │                    │  │\n│  │  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘  └──────┬──────┘                    │  │\n│  │         │                │                │                            │  │\n│  │         │                ▼                ▼                            │  │\n│  │         │         ┌──────────────┐  ┌──────────────┐                  │  │\n│  │         │         │ Timeout: 15m │  │ Timeout: 30m │                  │  │\n│  │         │         │ DELETE       │  │ DELETE       │                  │  │\n│  │         │         └──────────────┘  └──────────────┘                  │  │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                      Agentd Controller (Idle Cleanup)                        │\n│  ┌────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │\n│  │                      Reconciliation Loop                                │  │\n│  │  ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌─────────────┐   ┌───────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │    Get      │──►│   Check     │──►│  Calculate  │──►│  Delete   │  │  │\n│  │  │   AgentRun  │   │ IdleTimeout │   │  Remaining  │   │  if Idle  │  │  │\n│  │  │   time      │   │   Config    │   │   Time      │   │  Timeout  │  │  │\n│  │  └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └─────────────┘   └───────────┘  │  │\n│  │         │                │                │                │          │  │\n│  │         ▼                ▼                ▼                ▼          │  │\n│  │  ┌──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐  │  │\n│  │  │                    Requeue Decision                              │  │  │\n│  │  │  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐  ┌─────────────┐              │  │  │\n│  │  │  │  No Timeout │  │   Idle      │  │   Error     │              │  │  │\n│  │  │  │  Configured │  │   Detected  │  │   Occurred  │              │  │  │\n│  │  │  │  ──► Skip   │  │  ──► Delete │  │  ──► Requeue│              │  │  │\n│  │  │  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘  └─────────────┘              │  │  │\n│  │  └──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │  │\n│  └────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘  │\n├─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┤\n│                      Client-Go Integration Layer                             │\n│  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────┐  ┌──────────────────────────┐   │\n│  │  AgentRuntime    │  │  Typed Client    │  │  Status Subresource      │   │\n│  │  Interface       │  │  (v1alpha1)      │  │  (Get/Update)            │   │\n│  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────┘  └──────────────────────────┘   │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Architecture\n\n```\n┌─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┐\n│                     Idle Cleanup Controller Flow                             │\n│                                                                              │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  Watch   │──►│  Reconcile│──►│   Get    │──►│  Parse   │──►│  Check   │  │\n│  │  Events  │   │  Request  │   │  AgentRun │   │  Timeout │   │  Activity│  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   │  time     │   │  Config  │   │  Time    │  │\n│                                └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └────┬─────┘  │\n│                                                                     │        │\n│                          ┌──────────────────────────────────────────┘        │\n│                          │                                                   │\n│                          ▼                                                   │\n│  ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐   ┌──────────┐  │\n│  │  Return  │◀──│  Schedule│◀──│  Delete  │◀──│  Expired │◀──│Calculate │  │\n│  │  Result  │   │  Requeue │   │  Resource│   │  ?       │   │Idle Time │  │\n│  └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘   └──────────┘  │\n│                                                                              │\n└─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────┘\n```\n\n### Component Interactions\n\n| Component | Purpose | Input | Output |\n|-----------|---------|-------|--------|\n| **Reconciler** | Core reconciliation logic for AgentRuntime | context.Context, reconcile.Request | reconcile.Result, error |\n| **AgentRuntimeInterface** | Typed client for AgentRuntime CRUD | AgentRuntime objects | AgentRuntime operations |\n| **IdleTimeoutChecker** | Determines if resource has exceeded idle timeout | AgentRuntime status | bool (expired), time.Duration (remaining) |\n| **CleanupExecutor** | Performs the deletion of expired resources | AgentRuntime reference | error |\n| **RequeueCalculator** | Calculates next requeue time | remaining duration | reconcile.Result |\n\n---\n\n## Directory Structure\n\n```\npkg/agentd/\n├── controller.go         # Main reconciler implementation (~180 lines)\n├── controller_test.go    # Unit tests for reconciler (~200 lines)\n├── config.go             # Controller configuration (~80 lines)\n├── metrics.go            # Prometheus metrics for cleanup operations (~60 lines)\n└── doc.go                # Package documentation (~20 lines)\n\ncmd/agentd/\n└── main.go               # Controller entry point (~100 lines)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Data Structures\n\n### Domain Types\n\n#### Reconciler\n\n```go\n// Reconciler reconciles AgentRuntime objects for idle cleanup.\ntype Reconciler struct {\n    // Client is the Kubernetes client for AgentRuntime resources\n    client client.Client\n    \n    // Scheme is the runtime scheme for type registration\n    Scheme *runtime.Scheme\n    \n    // Clock provides time functionality (allows mocking in tests)\n    Clock Clock\n    \n    // Metrics collects operational metrics\n    Metrics *Metrics\n}\n\n// Clock abstracts time operations for testability.\ntype Clock interface {\n    Now() time.Time\n}\n\n// realClock implements Clock using the system clock.\ntype realClock struct{}\n\nfunc (c *realClock) Now() time.Time {\n    return time.Now()\n}\n\n// NewReconciler creates a new AgentRuntime idle cleanup reconciler.\nfunc NewReconciler(client client.Client, scheme *runtime.Scheme) *Reconciler {\n    return &Reconciler{\n        Client:  client,\n        Scheme:  scheme,\n        Clock:   &realClock{},\n        Metrics: newMetrics(),\n    }\n}\n```\n\n#### IdleTimeoutConfig\n\n```go\n// IdleTimeoutConfig holds the idle timeout configuration.\ntype IdleTimeoutConfig struct {\n    // DefaultTimeout is the fallback timeout when not specified in spec\n    DefaultTimeout time.Duration\n    \n    // MaxTimeout is the maximum allowed idle timeout\n    MaxTimeout time.Duration\n    \n    // MinTimeout is the minimum allowed idle timeout\n    MinTimeout time.Duration\n}\n\n// DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig returns the default configuration.\nfunc DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig() IdleTimeoutConfig {\n    return IdleTimeoutConfig{\n        DefaultTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n        MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n        MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n    }\n}\n\n// Validate checks if the configuration is valid.\nfunc (c *IdleTimeoutConfig) Validate() error {\n    if c.DefaultTimeout < c.MinTimeout {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"default timeout %v is less than minimum %v\", \n            c.DefaultTimeout, c.MinTimeout)\n    }\n    if c.DefaultTimeout > c.MaxTimeout {\n        return fmt.Errorf(\"default timeout %v is greater than maximum %v\",\n            c.DefaultTimeout, c.MaxTimeout)\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n#### CleanupResult\n\n```go\n// CleanupResult represents the outcome of a cleanup check.\ntype CleanupResult struct {\n    // ShouldDelete indicates whether the resource should be deleted\n    ShouldDelete bool\n    \n    // Reason provides a human-readable explanation\n    Reason string\n    \n    // IdleDuration is how long the resource has been idle\n    IdleDuration time.Duration\n    \n    // TimeoutDuration is the configured timeout\n    TimeoutDuration time.Duration\n    \n    // RemainingTime is time until cleanup (zero if ShouldDelete)\n    RemainingTime time.Duration\n}\n\n// String returns a string representation of the result.\nfunc (r *CleanupResult) String() string {\n    if r.ShouldDelete {\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"cleanup: %s (idle %v, timeout %v)\", \n            r.Reason, r.IdleDuration, r.TimeoutDuration)\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"skip: %s (idle %v, remaining %v)\",\n        r.Reason, r.IdleDuration, r.RemainingTime)\n}\n```\n\n### Request/Response Types\n\n#### ReconcileRequest (Internal)\n\n```go\n// ReconcileRequest wraps controller-runtime's reconcile.Request.\ntype ReconcileRequest struct {\n    // NamespacedName identifies the AgentRuntime resource\n    NamespacedName types.NamespacedName\n}\n\n// ToControllerRuntime converts to controller-runtime request.\nfunc (r *ReconcileRequest) ToControllerRuntime() reconcile.Request {\n    return reconcile.Request{NamespacedName: r.NamespacedName}\n}\n```\n\n### Internal Types\n\n#### ControllerConfig\n\n```go\n// ControllerConfig contains environment-based configuration.\ntype ControllerConfig struct {\n    // LeaderElection enables leader election for HA\n    LeaderElection bool\n    \n    // SyncPeriod is the period for full re-listing of resources\n    SyncPeriod time.Duration\n    \n    // WorkerCount is the number of concurrent reconcile workers\n    WorkerCount int\n    \n    // IdleTimeout is the default idle timeout configuration\n    IdleTimeout IdleTimeoutConfig\n    \n    // MetricsBindAddress is the address for metrics server (\":8080\" or \"0\" to disable)\n    MetricsBindAddress string\n    \n    // HealthProbeBindAddress is the address for health probes (\":8081\" or \"0\" to disable)\n    HealthProbeBindAddress string\n}\n\n// LoadConfig loads configuration from environment variables.\nfunc LoadConfig() (*ControllerConfig, error) {\n    cfg := &ControllerConfig{\n        LeaderElection:         getEnvBool(\"AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION\", true),\n        SyncPeriod:             getEnvDuration(\"AGENTD_SYNC_PERIOD\", 10*time.Minute),\n        WorkerCount:            getEnvInt(\"AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT\", 1),\n        IdleTimeout:            DefaultIdleTimeoutConfig(),\n        MetricsBindAddress:     getEnvOrDefault(\"AGENTD_METRICS_BIND_ADDRESS\", \"0\"),\n        HealthProbeBindAddress: getEnvOrDefault(\"AGENTD_HEALTH_PROBE_BIND_ADDRESS\", \"0\"),\n    }\n    \n    // Override idle timeout from env if specified\n    if timeout := os.Getenv(\"AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT\"); timeout != \"\" {\n        if d, err := time.ParseDuration(timeout); err == nil {\n            cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout = d\n        } else {\n            return nil, fmt.Errorf(\"invalid AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT: %v\", err)\n        }\n    }\n    \n    if err := cfg.IdleTimeout.Validate(); err != nil {\n        return nil, err\n    }\n    \n    return cfg, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Metrics\n\n```go\n// Metrics holds Prometheus metrics for the controller.\ntype Metrics struct {\n    // ReconcileTotal is the total number of reconciliations\n    ReconcileTotal prometheus.Counter\n    \n    // ReconcileErrors is the total number of reconciliation errors\n    ReconcileErrors prometheus.Counter\n    \n    // CleanupTotal is the total number of successful cleanups\n    CleanupTotal prometheus.Counter\n    \n    // CleanupDuration is the duration of cleanup operations\n    CleanupDuration prometheus.Histogram\n    \n    // IdleDuration is the idle duration of cleaned resources\n    IdleDuration prometheus.Histogram\n}\n\n// newMetrics creates a new Metrics instance.\nfunc newMetrics() *Metrics {\n    return &Metrics{\n        ReconcileTotal: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_reconcile_total\",\n            Help: \"Total number of idle cleanup reconciliations\",\n        }),\n        ReconcileErrors: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_reconcile_errors_total\",\n            Help: \"Total number of idle cleanup reconciliation errors\",\n        }),\n        CleanupTotal: prometheus.NewCounter(prometheus.CounterOpts{\n            Name: \"agentd_idle_cleanup_total\",\n            Help: \"Total number of idle cleanups performed\",\n        }),\n        CleanupDuration: prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n            Name:    \"agentd_idle_cleanup_duration_seconds\",\n            Help:    \"Duration of idle cleanup operations\",\n            Buckets: prometheus.DefBuckets,\n        }),\n        IdleDuration: prometheus.NewHistogram(prometheus.HistogramOpts{\n            Name:    \"agentd_idle_cleanup_idle_duration_seconds\",\n            Help:    \"Idle duration of cleaned resources\",\n            Buckets: []float64{60, 300, 600, 1800, 3600, 7200, 86400},\n        }),\n    }\n}\n\n// Register registers metrics with the provided registry.\nfunc (m *Metrics) Register(reg prometheus.Registerer) error {\n    collectors := []prometheus.Collector{\n        m.ReconcileTotal,\n        m.ReconcileErrors,\n        m.CleanupTotal,\n        m.CleanupDuration,\n        m.IdleDuration,\n    }\n    for _, c := range collectors {\n        if err := reg.Register(c); err != nil {\n            return err\n        }\n    }\n    return nil\n}\n```\n\n### Constants\n\n```go\n// Default configuration values\nconst (\n    // DefaultIdleTimeout is the default idle timeout when not specified\n    DefaultIdleTimeout = 15 * time.Minute\n    \n    // DefaultRequeueInterval is the default interval for requeuing when error occurs\n    DefaultRequeueInterval = 30 * time.Second\n    \n    // MinRequeueInterval is the minimum requeue interval\n    MinRequeueInterval = 5 * time.Second\n)\n\n// Error reasons for status updates\nconst (\n    // ReasonIdleTimeout indicates cleanup due to idle timeout\n    ReasonIdleTimeout = \"IdleTimeoutExceeded\"\n    \n    // ReasonNoIdleConfig indicates no idle timeout configured\n    ReasonNoIdleConfig = \"NoIdleTimeoutConfigured\"\n    \n    // ReasonActive indicates resource is still active\n    ReasonActive = \"ResourceStillActive\"\n)\n\n// Event types\nconst (\n    // EventTypeNormal indicates a normal event\n    EventTypeNormal = \"Normal\"\n    \n    // EventTypeWarning indicates a warning event\n    EventTypeWarning = \"Warning\"\n)\n\n// Event reasons\nconst (\n    // EventReasonIdleCleanup indicates successful idle cleanup\n    EventReasonIdleCleanup = \"IdleCleanup\"\n    \n    // EventReasonCleanupFailed indicates failed cleanup\n    EventReasonCleanupFailed = \"CleanupFailed\"\n)\n```\n\n---\n\n## API Contracts\n\n### Reconciler Interface\n\n```go\n// ReconcilerInterface defines the interface for AgentRuntime reconciliation.\ntype ReconcilerInterface interface {\n    // Reconcile performs idle cleanup reconciliation for the given AgentRuntime.\n    //\n    // Parameters:\n    //   - ctx: Context for cancellation and timeouts\n    //   - req: Reconcile request containing the AgentRuntime namespaced name\n    //\n    // Returns:\n    //   - reconcile.Result: Indicates whether to requeue and when\n    //   - error: Non-nil if reconciliation failed (triggers requeue with backoff)\n    //\n    // Behavior:\n    //   1. Fetch AgentRuntime from Kubernetes API\n    //   2. Check if IdleTimeoutSeconds is configured in spec\n    //   3. Parse LastActivityTime from status\n    //   4. Calculate idle duration\n    //   5. If idle duration > timeout, delete the resource\n    //   6. Otherwise, requeue after remaining time\n    Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error)\n}\n\n// SetupWithManager sets up the reconciler with the controller manager.\nfunc (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n    return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n        For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).\n        WithEventFilter(predicate.GenerationChangedPredicate{}).\n        Complete(r)\n}\n```\n\n### Idle Timeout Checker\n\n```go\n// CheckIdleTimeout determines if an AgentRuntime has exceeded its idle timeout.\n//\n// Parameters:\n//   - agentRuntime: The AgentRuntime to check\n//   - now: Current time\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - *CleanupResult: Result indicating whether cleanup should occur\n//   - error: If status fields cannot be parsed\n//\n// Logic:\n//   1. If IdleTimeoutSeconds is nil/0, return ShouldDelete=false (no timeout configured)\n//   2. If LastActivityTime is nil, use creation timestamp\n//   3. Calculate idleDuration = now - lastActivityTime\n//   4. timeoutDuration = IdleTimeoutSeconds converted to time.Duration\n//   5. If idleDuration >= timeoutDuration, return ShouldDelete=true\n//   6. Otherwise, return ShouldDelete=false with RemainingTime = timeoutDuration - idleDuration\nfunc CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime, now time.Time) (*CleanupResult, error)\n```\n\n### Cleanup Executor\n\n```go\n// ExecuteCleanup deletes an AgentRuntime that has exceeded its idle timeout.\n//\n// Parameters:\n//   - ctx: Context for the delete operation\n//   - client: Kubernetes client\n//   - agentRuntime: The AgentRuntime to delete\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - error: nil if deletion initiated successfully, otherwise error\n//\n// Notes:\n//   - Uses foreground deletion for graceful cleanup\n//   - Sets deletion reason annotation before deletion\nfunc ExecuteCleanup(ctx context.Context, client client.Client, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) error\n```\n\n### Configuration Functions\n\n```go\n// LoadConfig loads controller configuration from environment variables.\n//\n// Required: None (all have defaults)\n//\n// Optional environment variables:\n//   - AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION: Enable leader election (default: \"true\")\n//   - AGENTD_SYNC_PERIOD: Full re-list period (default: \"10m\")\n//   - AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT: Concurrent workers (default: \"1\")\n//   - AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT: Default idle timeout (default: \"15m\")\n//   - AGENTD_METRICS_BIND_ADDRESS: Metrics server address (default: \"0\")\n//   - AGENTD_HEALTH_PROBE_BIND_ADDRESS: Health probe address (default: \"0\")\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - *ControllerConfig: Loaded configuration\n//   - error: If configuration is invalid\nfunc LoadConfig() (*ControllerConfig, error)\n\n// GetTimeoutDuration extracts timeout duration from AgentRuntime spec.\n//\n// Returns:\n//   - time.Duration: The idle timeout duration\n//   - bool: true if timeout is configured, false otherwise\nfunc GetTimeoutDuration(spec *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec, defaults IdleTimeoutConfig) (time.Duration, bool)\n```\n\n### Metrics Functions\n\n```go\n// RecordReconcile records a reconciliation attempt.\nfunc (m *Metrics) RecordReconcile()\n\n// RecordReconcileError records a reconciliation error.\nfunc (m *Metrics) RecordReconcileError()\n\n// RecordCleanup records a successful cleanup.\nfunc (m *Metrics) RecordCleanup(duration time.Duration, idleDuration time.Duration)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Error Handling\n\n### Error Categories and Codes\n\n| Error | Code | Description | Retryable | Handling Strategy |\n|-------|------|-------------|-----------|-------------------|\n| `ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound` | `NOT_FOUND` | AgentRuntime was deleted | No | Return success (no requeue) |\n| `ErrGetAgentRuntimeFailed` | `GET_FAILED` | Failed to fetch AgentRuntime | Yes | Requeue with backoff |\n| `ErrParseLastActivity` | `PARSE_FAILED` | Failed to parse LastActivityTime | No | Log and skip resource |\n| `ErrDeleteFailed` | `DELETE_FAILED` | Deletion API call failed | Yes | Requeue with backoff |\n| `ErrInvalidTimeout` | `INVALID_TIMEOUT` | IdleTimeoutSeconds invalid | No | Log and skip resource |\n\n### Sentinel Errors\n\n```go\n// Controller errors\nvar (\n    ErrAgentRuntimeNotFound = errors.New(\"agentruntime: resource not found\")\n    ErrGetAgentRuntimeFailed = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to get resource\")\n    ErrParseLastActivity = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to parse last activity time\")\n    ErrDeleteFailed = errors.New(\"agentruntime: failed to delete resource\")\n    ErrInvalidTimeout = errors.New(\"agentruntime: invalid idle timeout configuration\")\n)\n```\n\n### Error Structures\n\n```go\n// ReconcileError represents a reconciliation error with context.\ntype ReconcileError struct {\n    // Code is the machine-readable error code\n    Code string `json:\"code\"`\n    \n    // Message is the human-readable error message\n    Message string `json:\"message\"`\n    \n    // Resource is the namespaced name of the affected resource\n    Resource types.NamespacedName `json:\"resource\"`\n    \n    // Retryable indicates if the error is retryable\n    Retryable bool `json:\"retryable\"`\n    \n    // underlying is the wrapped error\n    underlying error\n}\n\n// Error returns the error string.\nfunc (e *ReconcileError) Error() string {\n    if e.underlying != nil {\n        return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (resource: %s): %v\", \n            e.Code, e.Message, e.Resource, e.underlying)\n    }\n    return fmt.Sprintf(\"%s: %s (resource: %s)\", e.Code, e.Message, e.Resource)\n}\n\n// Unwrap returns the wrapped error.\nfunc (e *ReconcileError) Unwrap() error {\n    return e.underlying\n}\n\n// IsRetryable returns true if the error is retryable.\nfunc (e *ReconcileError) IsRetryable() bool {\n    return e.Retryable\n}\n\n// NewReconcileError creates a new ReconcileError.\nfunc NewReconcileError(code, message string, resource types.NamespacedName, retryable bool, underlying error) *ReconcileError {\n    return &ReconcileError{\n        Code:       code,\n        Message:    message,\n        Resource:   resource,\n        Retryable:  retryable,\n        underlying: underlying,\n    }\n}\n```\n\n### Error Handling Patterns\n\n#### Reconcile Error Handling\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) Reconcile(ctx context.Context, req reconcile.Request) (reconcile.Result, error) {\n    r.Metrics.RecordReconcile()\n    \n    log := log.FromContext(ctx).WithValues(\"agentruntime\", req.NamespacedName)\n    \n    // Fetch AgentRuntime\n    agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}\n    if err := r.client.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, agentRuntime); err != nil {\n        if errors.IsNotFound(err) {\n            log.Info(\"AgentRuntime not found, skipping\")\n            return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n        }\n        r.Metrics.RecordReconcileError()\n        return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n            \"GET_FAILED\",\n            \"failed to get AgentRuntime\",\n            req.NamespacedName,\n            true,\n            err,\n        )\n    }\n    \n    // Check idle timeout\n    result, err := r.checkAndCleanup(ctx, agentRuntime)\n    if err != nil {\n        r.Metrics.RecordReconcileError()\n        reconcileErr, ok := err.(*ReconcileError)\n        if ok && !reconcileErr.IsRetryable() {\n            log.Error(err, \"Non-retryable error during cleanup, skipping\")\n            return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n        }\n        return reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: DefaultRequeueInterval}, err\n    }\n    \n    return result, nil\n}\n```\n\n#### Check and Cleanup Pattern\n\n```go\nfunc (r *Reconciler) checkAndCleanup(ctx context.Context, agentRuntime *runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime) (reconcile.Result, error) {\n    log := log.FromContext(ctx)\n    \n    // Check idle timeout\n    cleanupResult, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, r.Clock.Now())\n    if err != nil {\n        return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n            \"PARSE_FAILED\",\n            \"failed to check idle timeout\",\n            types.NamespacedName{Name: agentRuntime.Name, Namespace: agentRuntime.Namespace},\n            false,\n            err,\n        )\n    }\n    \n    log.V(1).Info(\"Idle check result\", \"result\", cleanupResult.String())\n    \n    // If should delete, execute cleanup\n    if cleanupResult.ShouldDelete {\n        start := r.Clock.Now()\n        if err := ExecuteCleanup(ctx, r.client, agentRuntime); err != nil {\n            return reconcile.Result{}, NewReconcileError(\n                \"DELETE_FAILED\",\n                \"failed to delete idle AgentRuntime\",\n                types.NamespacedName{Name: agentRuntime.Name, Namespace: agentRuntime.Namespace},\n                true,\n                err,\n            )\n        }\n        \n        duration := r.Clock.Now().Sub(start)\n        r.Metrics.RecordCleanup(duration, cleanupResult.IdleDuration)\n        log.Info(\"Deleted idle AgentRuntime\",\n            \"idleDuration\", cleanupResult.IdleDuration,\n            \"timeoutDuration\", cleanupResult.TimeoutDuration)\n        \n        return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n    }\n    \n    // Requeue after remaining time\n    if cleanupResult.RemainingTime > 0 {\n        // Add small buffer to avoid race conditions\n        requeueAfter := cleanupResult.RemainingTime + MinRequeueInterval\n        log.V(1).Info(\"Requeuing for next idle check\",\n            \"requeueAfter\", requeueAfter,\n            \"remainingTime\", cleanupResult.RemainingTime)\n        return reconcile.Result{RequeueAfter: requeueAfter}, nil\n    }\n    \n    return reconcile.Result{}, nil\n}\n```\n\n---\n\n## Testing Strategy\n\n### Unit Tests\n\n#### controller_test.go\n\n```go\nfunc TestReconciler_Reconcile_NotFound(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup\n    client := fake.NewClientBuilder().Build()\n    reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n    \n    // Execute - resource doesn't exist\n    result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n        NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n    })\n    \n    // Assert\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n    assert.Equal(t, time.Duration(0), result.RequeueAfter)\n}\n\nfunc TestReconciler_Reconcile_NoIdleTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup - AgentRuntime without idle timeout\n    agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"test\",\n            Namespace: \"default\",\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            // IdleTimeoutSeconds not set\n        },\n    }\n    \n    client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n    reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n    \n    // Execute\n    result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n        NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n    })\n    \n    // Assert - should not requeue, no timeout configured\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n    \n    // Verify resource still exists\n    err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n}\n\nfunc TestReconciler_Reconcile_IdleTimeoutNotExpired(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup\n    now := time.Now()\n    lastActivity := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-5 * time.Minute)) // 5 minutes ago\n    \n    agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"test\",\n            Namespace: \"default\",\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n        },\n        Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n            LastActivityTime: &lastActivity,\n        },\n    }\n    \n    client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n    reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n    reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n    \n    // Execute\n    result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n        NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n    })\n    \n    // Assert - should requeue after ~10 minutes\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.InDelta(t, 10*time.Minute, result.RequeueAfter, float64(time.Minute))\n    \n    // Verify resource still exists\n    err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n}\n\nfunc TestReconciler_Reconcile_IdleTimeoutExpired(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup\n    now := time.Now()\n    lastActivity := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-30 * time.Minute)) // 30 minutes ago\n    \n    agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"test\",\n            Namespace: \"default\",\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n        },\n        Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n            LastActivityTime: &lastActivity,\n        },\n    }\n    \n    client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n    reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n    reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n    \n    // Execute\n    result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n        NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n    })\n    \n    // Assert - should not requeue, resource deleted\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n    \n    // Verify resource deleted\n    err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n    require.Error(t, err)\n    assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n}\n\nfunc TestReconciler_Reconcile_NoLastActivityTime(t *testing.T) {\n    // Setup - no LastActivityTime, should use creation time\n    now := time.Now()\n    creationTime := metav1.NewTime(now.Add(-20 * time.Minute))\n    \n    agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:              \"test\",\n            Namespace:         \"default\",\n            CreationTimestamp: creationTime,\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](900), // 15 minutes\n        },\n        Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n            // LastActivityTime not set\n        },\n    }\n    \n    client := fake.NewClientBuilder().WithObjects(agentRuntime).Build()\n    reconciler := NewReconciler(client, scheme.Scheme)\n    reconciler.Clock = &fakeClock{now: now}\n    \n    // Execute\n    result, err := reconciler.Reconcile(context.Background(), reconcile.Request{\n        NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n    })\n    \n    // Assert - should delete based on creation time\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.False(t, result.Requeue)\n    \n    // Verify resource deleted\n    err = client.Get(context.Background(), types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n    require.Error(t, err)\n    assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n}\n\nfunc TestCheckIdleTimeout_NoTimeout(t *testing.T) {\n    now := time.Now()\n    agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            // IdleTimeoutSeconds not set\n        },\n        Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n            LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-1 * time.Hour)},\n        },\n    }\n    \n    result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.False(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"no idle timeout configured\", result.Reason)\n}\n\nfunc TestCheckIdleTimeout_NotExpired(t *testing.T) {\n    now := time.Now()\n    agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](1800), // 30 minutes\n        },\n        Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n            LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-10 * time.Minute)},\n        },\n    }\n    \n    result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.False(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n    assert.InDelta(t, 20*time.Minute, result.RemainingTime, float64(time.Second))\n}\n\nfunc TestCheckIdleTimeout_Expired(t *testing.T) {\n    now := time.Now()\n    agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](600), // 10 minutes\n        },\n        Status: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeStatus{\n            LastActivityTime: &metav1.Time{Time: now.Add(-15 * time.Minute)},\n        },\n    }\n    \n    result, err := CheckIdleTimeout(agentRuntime, now)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    assert.True(t, result.ShouldDelete)\n    assert.Equal(t, \"idle timeout exceeded\", result.Reason)\n    assert.InDelta(t, 15*time.Minute, result.IdleDuration, float64(time.Second))\n}\n\n// fakeClock implements Clock for testing\ntype fakeClock struct {\n    now time.Time\n}\n\nfunc (c *fakeClock) Now() time.Time {\n    return c.now\n}\n```\n\n#### config_test.go\n\n```go\nfunc TestLoadConfig_Defaults(t *testing.T) {\n    cfg, err := LoadConfig()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    assert.True(t, cfg.LeaderElection)\n    assert.Equal(t, 10*time.Minute, cfg.SyncPeriod)\n    assert.Equal(t, 1, cfg.WorkerCount)\n    assert.Equal(t, 15*time.Minute, cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout)\n}\n\nfunc TestLoadConfig_FromEnv(t *testing.T) {\n    t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_IDLE_TIMEOUT\", \"30m\")\n    t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_WORKER_COUNT\", \"5\")\n    t.Setenv(\"AGENTD_LEADER_ELECTION\", \"false\")\n    \n    cfg, err := LoadConfig()\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    assert.Equal(t, 30*time.Minute, cfg.IdleTimeout.DefaultTimeout)\n    assert.Equal(t, 5, cfg.WorkerCount)\n    assert.False(t, cfg.LeaderElection)\n}\n\nfunc TestIdleTimeoutConfig_Validate(t *testing.T) {\n    // Valid config\n    validConfig := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n        DefaultTimeout: 15 * time.Minute,\n        MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n        MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n    }\n    require.NoError(t, validConfig.Validate())\n    \n    // Invalid: default < min\n    invalidConfig1 := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n        DefaultTimeout: 30 * time.Second,\n        MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n        MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n    }\n    require.Error(t, invalidConfig1.Validate())\n    \n    // Invalid: default > max\n    invalidConfig2 := IdleTimeoutConfig{\n        DefaultTimeout: 48 * time.Hour,\n        MinTimeout:     1 * time.Minute,\n        MaxTimeout:     24 * time.Hour,\n    }\n    require.Error(t, invalidConfig2.Validate())\n}\n```\n\n### Integration Tests\n\n```go\nfunc TestIntegration_Controller(t *testing.T) {\n    if testing.Short() {\n        t.Skip(\"Skipping integration test\")\n    }\n    \n    // Setup test environment\n    cfg := &rest.Config{Host: os.Getenv(\"KUBECONFIG\")}\n    scheme := runtime.NewScheme()\n    require.NoError(t, runtimev1alpha1.AddToScheme(scheme))\n    \n    // Create manager\n    mgr, err := ctrl.NewManager(cfg, ctrl.Options{\n        Scheme: scheme,\n    })\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Setup reconciler\n    reconciler := NewReconciler(mgr.GetClient(), mgr.GetScheme())\n    require.NoError(t, reconciler.SetupWithManager(mgr))\n    \n    // Create test AgentRuntime\n    ctx := context.Background()\n    agentRuntime := &runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{\n        ObjectMeta: metav1.ObjectMeta{\n            Name:      \"test-idle-cleanup\",\n            Namespace: \"default\",\n        },\n        Spec: runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntimeSpec{\n            Image:              \"test:latest\",\n            IdleTimeoutSeconds: ptr.To[int32](60), // 1 minute\n        },\n    }\n    \n    err = mgr.GetClient().Create(ctx, agentRuntime)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Update status with old last activity time\n    agentRuntime.Status.LastActivityTime = &metav1.Time{\n        Time: time.Now().Add(-2 * time.Minute), // 2 minutes ago\n    }\n    err = mgr.GetClient().Status().Update(ctx, agentRuntime)\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Trigger reconciliation\n    _, err = reconciler.Reconcile(ctx, reconcile.Request{\n        NamespacedName: types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test-idle-cleanup\", Namespace: \"default\"},\n    })\n    require.NoError(t, err)\n    \n    // Verify deletion\n    err = mgr.GetClient().Get(ctx, types.NamespacedName{Name: \"test-idle-cleanup\", Namespace: \"default\"}, agentRuntime)\n    require.Error(t, err)\n    assert.True(t, errors.IsNotFound(err))\n}\n```\n\n### Test Execution\n\n```bash\n# Run all controller tests\nmake test PKG=./pkg/agentd/...\n\n# Run with race detector\ngo test -race ./pkg/agentd/...\n\n# Run specific test categories\ngo test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestReconciler\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestCheckIdleTimeout\"\ngo test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -run \"TestLoadConfig\"\n\n# With coverage\ngo test ./pkg/agentd/... -coverprofile=coverage.out\ngo tool cover -html=coverage.out\n\n# Integration tests (requires k8s cluster)\ngo test -v ./pkg/agentd/... -tags=integration\n```\n\n---\n\n## Security Considerations\n\n### Resource Deletion\n\n- Deletion uses foreground propagation for graceful cleanup\n- Only deletes resources in the same namespace the controller has access to\n- RBAC rules must be carefully configured to allow only delete on AgentRuntime\n- Audit logging should be enabled for deletion events\n\n### RBAC Requirements\n\n```yaml\napiVersion: rbac.authorization.k8s.io/v1\nkind: ClusterRole\nmetadata:\n  name: agentd-idle-cleanup\nrules:\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\", \"list\", \"watch\", \"delete\"]\n- apiGroups: [\"runtime.agentcube.volcano.sh\"]\n  resources: [\"agentruntimes/status\"]\n  verbs: [\"get\"]\n```\n\n### Time Safety\n\n- Clock skew between controller and API server is handled via configurable tolerance\n- Time comparisons use monotonic clocks where available\n- Leap seconds are handled gracefully\n\n### Logging Safety\n\n- Resource names and namespaces are logged at appropriate levels\n- No sensitive data (tokens, credentials) is logged\n- Log levels: DEBUG (V(2)) for timing details, INFO for deletions, WARN for errors\n\n---\n\n## Performance Considerations\n\n### Scalability\n\n| Metric | Target | Notes |\n|--------|--------|-------|\n| Reconcile latency | < 100ms | P99 for single resource |\n| Concurrent reconciles | 10+ | Configurable via worker count |\n| Memory per resource | < 1KB | Minimal resource footprint |\n| API calls per reconcile | 1-2 | Get + optional Delete |\n\n### Optimization Strategies\n\n- Single API call per reconcile (Get only, Delete only when needed)\n- Precise requeue timing based on remaining idle time\n- No polling - event-driven reconciliation\n- Minimal memory allocation in hot path\n- Shared informer cache for reduced API server load\n\n### Resource Usage\n\n- **Memory**: Scales with number of AgentRuntimes being watched\n- **CPU**: Low baseline, spikes during bulk reconciliations\n- **Network**: Minimal - only API calls for Get and Delete\n- **Storage**: None (no persistent storage)\n\n---\n\n## Integration Points\n\n### With AgentRuntime API\n\n```go\n// Watches AgentRuntime resources via controller-runtime\nfunc (r *Reconciler) SetupWithManager(mgr ctrl.Manager) error {\n    return ctrl.NewControllerManagedBy(mgr).\n        For(&runtimev1alpha1.AgentRuntime{}).\n        WithEventFilter(predicate.GenerationChangedPredicate{}).\n        Complete(r)\n}\n```\n\n### With client-go\n\n```go\n// Uses generated client for typed operations\nimport runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n\n// Get AgentRuntime using controller-runtime client (wrapper around client-go)\nerr := r.client.Get(ctx, req.NamespacedName, agentRuntime)\n```\n\n### With Workload Manager\n\nThe controller reads `LastActivityTime` which is updated by the workload manager:\n\n```go\n// LastActivityTime is set by workload manager when processing requests\nlastActivity := agentRuntime.Status.LastActivityTime\n```\n\n### With Metrics Server\n\n```go\n// Metrics are exposed for Prometheus scraping\nmetrics.Registry.MustRegister(reconciler.Metrics.ReconcileTotal)\nmetrics.Registry.MustRegister(reconciler.Metrics.CleanupTotal)\n```\n\n---\n\n## Dependencies\n\n```go\nimport (\n    \"context\"\n    \"errors\"\n    \"fmt\"\n    \"os\"\n    \"time\"\n    \n    \"github.com/prometheus/client_golang/prometheus\"\n    corev1 \"k8s.io/api/core/v1\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/api/errors\"\n    metav1 \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/apis/meta/v1\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/runtime\"\n    \"k8s.io/apimachinery/pkg/types\"\n    \"k8s.io/utils/ptr\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/client\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/log\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/manager\"\n    \"sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime/pkg/reconcile\"\n    \n    runtimev1alpha1 \"github.com/volcano-sh/agentcube/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1\"\n)\n```\n\n| Package | Purpose | Version |\n|---------|---------|---------|\n| `sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime` | Controller framework | v0.19.x |\n| `github.com/prometheus/client_golang` | Metrics | v1.20.x |\n| `k8s.io/api` | Kubernetes API types | v0.31.x |\n| `k8s.io/apimachinery` | Kubernetes utilities | v0.31.x |\n| `k8s.io/utils` | Kubernetes helpers | v0.0.x |\n\n---\n\n## References\n\n- [AgentRuntime Types](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go) — AgentRuntime CRD types\n- [client-go Spec](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/.sdd_prompt.md) — client-go library specification\n- [Idle Cleanup (Sandbox)](/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli-benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/idle-cleanup/design.md) — Related sandbox idle cleanup design\n- [controller-runtime](https://pkg.go.dev/sigs.k8s.io/controller-runtime) — Controller runtime documentation\n- [Kubernetes Controllers](https://kubernetes.io/docs/concepts/architecture/controller/) — Kubernetes controller patterns\n\n---\n\n*AR-018 — Module: pkg/agentd — Language: Go — Size: S*\n"},"output":"Wrote file successfully.","metadata":{"diagnostics":{"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/apis/runtime/v1alpha1/agentruntime_types.go":[],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/go.mod":[{"range":{"start":{"line":18,"character":42},"end":{"line":18,"character":53}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/alicebob/miniredis/v2 should be direct"},{"range":{"start":{"line":35,"character":31},"end":{"line":35,"character":42}},"severity":2,"source":"go mod tidy","message":"github.com/google/uuid should be direct"}],"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/pkg/workloadmanager/controller/reconciler.go":[]},"filepath":"/home/dsj/benchmark/workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","exists":true,"truncated":false},"title":"workspaces/v5.1/opencode-cli_bailian-coding-plan-kimi-k2.5_20260410T163138Z/design.md","time":{"start":1775880056191,"end":1775880056713}}}}
