{"type":"text","timestamp":1775880264277,"sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","part":{"id":"prt_d7ab5dd69001ZqXrywU2sizTsO","messageID":"msg_d7ab32fd1001HMZSQcvSJs2xI1","sessionID":"ses_285516e0bffe2PWxVwG32DaMa0","type":"text","text":"I've successfully written the `design.md` file with comprehensive technical implementation details for AR-018 — Agentd Idle Cleanup Controller. \n\nThe design document includes:\n\n1. **Overview** — Introduction to the idle cleanup controller and its purpose\n2. **Architecture** — High-level design diagrams showing the reconciliation flow and component interactions\n3. **Directory Structure** — File organization for `pkg/agentd/` and `cmd/agentd/`\n4. **Data Structures** — Complete type definitions including:\n   - `Reconciler` with `Clock` interface for testability\n   - `IdleTimeoutConfig` for timeout configuration\n   - `CleanupResult` for cleanup decisions\n   - `Metrics` for Prometheus integration\n   - Configuration and constants\n\n5. **API Contracts** — Detailed interface specifications for:\n   - `ReconcilerInterface.Reconcile()`\n   - `CheckIdleTimeout()` function\n   - `ExecuteCleanup()` function\n   - Configuration and metrics functions\n\n6. **Error Handling** — Error categories, sentinel errors, `ReconcileError` structure, and error handling patterns\n\n7. **Testing Strategy** — Comprehensive unit tests including:\n   - Reconciler tests (not found, no timeout, not expired, expired, no activity time)\n   - `CheckIdleTimeout` tests\n   - Config validation tests\n   - Integration test examples\n   - Test execution commands\n\n8. **Security Considerations** — RBAC requirements, time safety, logging safety\n\n9. **Performance Considerations** — Scalability targets, optimization strategies, resource usage\n\n10. **Integration Points** — How it integrates with AgentRuntime API, client-go, workload manager, and metrics\n\n11. **Dependencies** — Required Go packages and versions","time":{"start":1775880264273,"end":177588